01:55:21,840 --> 01:55:30,530
"I knew you would be here," Anne Nelson said
to her daughter as the three of them sat around

1871
01:55:30,530 --> 01:55:34,019
the coffee table in the living room.

1872
01:55:34,019 --> 01:55:37,019
"How could you be so sure?"

1873
01:55:37,019 --> 01:55:38,510
"You're my daughter.

1874
01:55:38,510 --> 01:55:45,000
One day when you have kids of your own, you'll
know the answer."

1875
01:55:45,000 --> 01:55:53,590
She smiled, but her manner was tense, and
Noah imagined how difficult this was for her.

1876
01:55:53,590 --> 01:55:56,429
"I saw the article, too, and I saw your reaction.

1877
01:55:56,429 --> 01:56:00,579
I also saw how nervous you've been during
the last couple of weeks, and when you said

1878
01:56:00,579 --> 01:56:04,150
you were going shopping near the coast, I
knew exactly what you meant."

1879
01:56:04,150 --> 01:56:05,409
"What about daddy?"

1880
01:56:05,409 --> 01:56:12,119
Anne Nelson shook her head, "No, I didn't
tell your father or anyone else about it.

1881
01:56:12,119 --> 01:56:15,739
Nor did I tell anyone where I was going today."

1882
01:56:15,739 --> 01:56:16,820
"Why did you come?"

1883
01:56:16,820 --> 01:56:17,820
Allie asked.

1884
01:56:17,820 --> 01:56:22,860
"I came because I had to," her mother said,
"Which I'm sure is the same reason you came.

1885
01:56:22,860 --> 01:56:23,860
Am I right?"

1886
01:56:23,860 --> 01:56:24,860
Allie nodded.

1887
01:56:24,860 --> 01:56:25,860
Anne turned to Noah.

1888
01:56:25,860 --> 01:56:29,500
"I know you don't think so, but I always liked
you.

1889
01:56:29,500 --> 01:56:32,820
I just didn't think you were right for my
daughter.

1890
01:56:32,820 --> 01:56:34,159
Can you understand that?"

1891
01:56:34,159 --> 01:56:37,750
He shook his head as he answered, "No, not
really.

1892
01:56:37,750 --> 01:56:41,760
It wasn't fair to me, and it wasn't fair to
Allie.

1893
01:56:41,760 --> 01:56:46,820
Otherwise she wouldn't be here."

1894
01:56:46,820 --> 01:56:53,309
She watched him as he spoke, but she said
nothing.

1895
01:56:53,309 --> 01:56:56,349
Allie, sensing an argument, cut in.

1896
01:56:56,349 --> 01:57:01,520
"What do you mean when you say you had to
come?

1897
01:57:01,520 --> 01:57:02,599
Don't you trust me?"

1898
01:57:02,599 --> 01:57:04,179
Anne turned back to her daughter.

1899
01:57:04,179 --> 01:57:05,760
"This has nothing to do with trust.

1900
01:57:05,760 --> 01:57:07,130
This has to do with Lon.

1901
01:57:07,130 --> 01:57:16,489
He called the house last night to talk to
me about Noah, and he's on his way here right

1902
01:57:16,489 --> 01:57:17,489
now.

1903
01:57:17,489 --> 01:57:18,900
He seemed very upset.

1904
01:57:18,900 --> 01:57:21,800
I thought you'd want to know."

1905
01:57:21,800 --> 01:57:23,239
Allie inhaled sharply.

1906
01:57:23,239 --> 01:57:25,170
"He's on his way?"

1907
01:57:25,170 --> 01:57:26,619
"As we speak.

1908
01:57:26,619 --> 01:57:30,340
He arranged to have the trial postponed until
next week.

1909
01:57:30,340 --> 01:57:33,530
If he's not in New Bern yet, he's close."

1910
01:57:33,530 --> 01:57:35,949
"What did you say to him?"

1911
01:57:35,949 --> 01:57:36,949
"Not much.

1912
01:57:36,949 --> 01:57:37,969
But he guessed.

1913
01:57:37,969 --> 01:57:42,130
He remembered my telling him about Noah a
long time ago."

1914
01:57:42,130 --> 01:57:48,619
Allie swallowed hard, and then asked, "Did
you tell him I was here?"

1915
01:57:48,619 --> 01:57:49,619
"No.

1916
01:57:49,619 --> 01:57:50,619
And I won't.

1917
01:57:50,619 --> 01:57:53,110
That's between you and him.

1918
01:57:53,110 --> 01:57:57,099
But knowing him, I'm sure he'll find you.

1919
01:57:57,099 --> 01:58:09,769
All it takes is a couple of phone calls to
the right people.

1920
01:58:09,769 --> 01:58:17,659
After all, I was able to find you."

1921
01:58:17,659 --> 01:58:22,119
Allie, though obviously tired, smiled at her
mother.

1922
01:58:22,119 --> 01:58:31,139
"Thank you," she said, and her mother reached
for her hand.

1923
01:58:31,139 --> 01:58:39,900
"I know we've had our differences, Allie,
and that we haven't seen eye to eye on everything.

1924
01:58:39,900 --> 01:58:45,559
But I'm your mother and that means I'll always
love you."

1925
01:58:45,559 --> 01:58:49,349
Allie was silent for a moment, and then asked,
"What should I do?"

1926
01:58:49,349 --> 01:58:50,530
"I don't know, Allie.

1927
01:58:50,530 --> 01:58:51,889
That's up to you.

1928
01:58:51,889 --> 01:58:54,219
But I would think about it.

1929
01:58:54,219 --> 01:58:56,550
Think about what you really want."

1930
01:58:56,550 --> 01:58:59,400
Allie turned away, her eyes were reddening.

1931
01:58:59,400 --> 01:59:04,199
A moment later, a tear drifted down her cheek.

1932
01:59:04,199 --> 01:59:05,789
"I don't know..."

1933
01:59:05,789 --> 01:59:08,460
Her mother squeezed her hand.

1934
01:59:08,460 --> 01:59:15,909
Anne looked at Noah, who had been sitting
with his head down, listening carefully.

1935
01:59:15,909 --> 01:59:22,210
As if reading her mind, he returned her gaze,
nodded and left the room.

1936
01:59:22,210 --> 01:59:26,980
When he was gone, Anne whispered, "Do you
love him?"

1937
01:59:26,980 --> 01:59:30,789
"Yes, I do," Allie answered softly, "very
much."

1938
01:59:30,789 --> 01:59:32,699
"Do you love Lon?"

1939
01:59:32,699 --> 01:59:34,130
"Yes, I do.

1940
01:59:34,130 --> 01:59:36,030
I love him, too.

1941
01:59:36,030 --> 01:59:38,889
Dearly, but in a different way.

1942
01:59:38,889 --> 01:59:42,090
He doesn't make me feel the way Noah does."

1943
01:59:42,090 --> 01:59:48,329
"No one will ever do that," her mother said,
and she released Allie's hand.

1944
01:59:48,329 --> 01:59:54,659
"I can't make this decision for you, Allie,
this one's all yours.

1945
01:59:54,659 --> 01:59:59,940
I want you to know, though, that I love you.

1946
01:59:59,940 --> 02:00:00,940
And I always will.

1947
02:00:00,940 --> 02:00:03,409
I know that doesn't help, but it's all I can
do."

1948
02:00:03,409 --> 02:00:09,960
She reached in her handbag and removed a packet
of letters held together with string; the

1949
02:00:09,960 --> 02:00:11,170
envelopes were old and slightly yellowed.

1950
02:00:11,170 --> 02:00:15,840
"These are the letters that Noah wrote to
you.

1951
02:00:15,840 --> 02:00:21,139
I never threw them away, and I didn't open
them.

1952
02:00:21,139 --> 02:00:27,369
I know, it was wrong of me to keep them from
you, and I'm sorry for that.

1953
02:00:27,369 --> 02:00:29,219
But I was just trying to protect you.

1954
02:00:29,219 --> 02:00:30,340
I didn't realize..."

1955
02:00:30,340 --> 02:00:34,070
Allie took them and ran her hand over them,
shocked.

1956
02:00:34,070 --> 02:00:35,560
"I should go, Allie.

1957
02:00:35,560 --> 02:00:40,040
You've got some decisions to make, and you
don't have much time.

1958
02:00:40,040 --> 02:00:43,409
Do you want me to stay in town?"

1959
02:00:43,409 --> 02:00:47,910
Allie shook her head, "No, this is up to me."

1960
02:00:47,910 --> 02:00:57,889
Anne nodded and watched her daughter for a
moment.

1961
02:00:57,889 --> 02:01:02,699
Finally, she stood, went around the table,
leaned over and kissed Allie on the cheek.

1962
02:01:02,699 --> 02:01:08,630
She could see the confusion in her daughter's
eyes as Allie embraced her.

1963
02:01:08,630 --> 02:01:13,409
They stood together for another minute, just
holding each other.

1964
02:01:13,409 --> 02:01:17,050
"Thanks for coming," Allie said, "I love you."

1965
02:01:17,050 --> 02:01:19,130
"I love you too."

1966
02:01:19,130 --> 02:01:26,280
As her mother left the living room, Allie
thought that she heard her whisper, "Follow

1967
02:01:26,280 --> 02:01:28,889
your heart," but she couldn't be sure.

1968
02:01:28,889 --> 02:01:32,559
NOAH OPENED the door for Anne Nelson as she
went out.

1969
02:01:32,559 --> 02:01:35,110
"Goodbye Noah," she said quietly.

1970
02:01:35,110 --> 02:01:37,150
He nodded without speaking.

1971
02:01:37,150 --> 02:01:42,239
There wasn't anything else to say; they both
knew that.

1972
02:01:42,239 --> 02:01:47,840
She turned from him and left, closing the
door behind her.

1973
02:01:47,840 --> 02:01:52,650
Noah watched her leave without looking back.

1974
02:01:52,650 --> 02:02:01,900
She was a strong woman, he thought to himself,
and he knew then where Allie got it.

1975
02:02:01,900 --> 02:02:09,250
Noah peeped into the living room, saw Allie
sitting with her head down, then went to the

1976
02:02:09,250 --> 02:02:13,800
back porch, knowing that she needed to be
alone.

1977
02:02:13,800 --> 02:02:18,860
He sat quietly in his rocker and watched the
water.

1978
02:02:18,860 --> 02:02:22,309
After a while, he heard the back door open.

1979
02:02:22,309 --> 02:02:27,252
He didn't turn to look at her - for some reason
he couldn't - and he listened as she sat in

1980
02:02:27,252 --> 02:02:28,252
the chair beside him.

1981
02:02:28,252 --> 02:02:29,252
"I'm sorry," Allie said, "I had no idea this
would happen."

1982
02:02:29,252 --> 02:02:30,252
Noah shook his head.

1983
02:02:30,252 --> 02:02:31,252
"Don't be sorry.

1984
02:02:31,252 --> 02:02:35,489
We both knew it was coming to some form or
another."

1985
02:02:35,489 --> 02:02:37,219
"It's still hard."

1986
02:02:37,219 --> 02:02:38,380
"I know."

1987
02:02:38,380 --> 02:02:40,590
He finally turned to her, reaching for her
hand.

1988
02:02:40,590 --> 02:02:48,650
"Is here anything I can do to make it easier?"

1989
02:02:48,650 --> 02:02:49,650
She shook her head.

1990
02:02:49,650 --> 02:02:50,650
"No.

1991
02:02:50,650 --> 02:02:51,650
Not really.

1992
02:02:51,650 --> 02:02:53,110
I have to do this alone.

1993
02:02:53,110 --> 02:02:57,750
Besides, I'm not sure what I'm going to say
to him yet."

1994
02:02:57,750 --> 02:03:02,659
She looked down and her voice became softer.

1995
02:03:02,659 --> 02:03:10,480
"I guess it depends on him and how much he
knows.

1996
02:03:10,480 --> 02:03:17,690
If my mother was right, he may have suspicions,
but he doesn't know anything for sure."

1997
02:03:17,690 --> 02:03:20,079
Noah felt tightness in his stomach.

1998
02:03:20,079 --> 02:03:26,960
When he finally spoke his voice was steady,
but she could hear the pain in it.

1999
02:03:26,960 --> 02:03:34,520
"You're not going to tell him about us, are
you?"

2000
02:03:34,520 --> 02:03:36,280
"I don't know.

2001
02:03:36,280 --> 02:03:38,039
I really don't.

2002
02:03:38,039 --> 02:03:50,030
While I was in the living room, I was asking
myself what I really wanted in my life."

2003
02:03:50,030 --> 02:03:52,280
She squeezed his hand.

2004
02:03:52,280 --> 02:03:58,280
"And do you know what the answer was?

2005
02:03:58,280 --> 02:04:02,749
The answer was that I want you.

2006
02:04:02,749 --> 02:04:03,780
I want us.

2007
02:04:03,780 --> 02:04:06,190
I love you and I always have."

2008
02:04:06,190 --> 02:04:09,739
She took a deep breath before going on.

2009
02:04:09,739 --> 02:04:15,269
"But I also want a happy ending without hurting
anyone.

2010
02:04:15,269 --> 02:04:19,369
And I know that if I stayed, people would
be hurt.

2011
02:04:19,369 --> 02:04:20,369
Especially Lon.

2012
02:04:20,369 --> 02:04:24,480
I wasn't lying when I told you that I love
him.

2013
02:04:24,480 --> 02:04:32,350
He doesn't make me feel the same way you do,
but I care for him, and this wouldn't be fair

2014
02:04:32,350 --> 02:04:33,350
to him.

2015
02:04:33,350 --> 02:04:36,560
Staying here would also hurt my family and
friends.

2016
02:04:36,560 --> 02:04:44,820
I would betray everyone I know... I don't
know if I can do that."

2017
02:04:44,820 --> 02:04:49,530
"You can't live your life for other people.

2018
02:04:49,530 --> 02:04:56,719
You've got to do what's right for you, even
if it hurts some people you love."

2019
02:04:56,719 --> 02:05:00,820
"I know," she said, "but no matter what I
choose I have to live with it.

2020
02:05:00,820 --> 02:05:01,820
Forever.

2021
02:05:01,820 --> 02:05:05,960
I have to be able to go forward and not look
back any more.

2022
02:05:05,960 --> 02:05:07,920
Can you understand that?"

2023
02:05:07,920 --> 02:05:12,420
He shook his head and tried to keep his voice
steady.

2024
02:05:12,420 --> 02:05:13,420
"Not really.

2025
02:05:13,420 --> 02:05:14,420
Not if it means losing you.

2026
02:05:14,420 --> 02:05:15,630
I can't do that again."

2027
02:05:15,630 --> 02:05:18,059
She didn't say anything but lowered her head.

2028
02:05:18,059 --> 02:05:21,389
Noah went on, "Could you really leave me without
looking back?"

2029
02:05:21,389 --> 02:05:23,520
She bit her lip as she answered.

2030
02:05:23,520 --> 02:05:24,520
"I don't know.

2031
02:05:24,520 --> 02:05:25,520
Probably not."

2032
02:05:25,520 --> 02:05:26,690
"Would that be fair to Lon?"

2033
02:05:26,690 --> 02:05:27,690
She didn't answer.

2034
02:05:27,690 --> 02:05:33,099
Instead, she stood up, wiped her face and
walked to the edge of the porch where she

2035
02:05:33,099 --> 02:05:37,239
leaned against the post and watched the water
before answering quietly: "No."

2036
02:05:37,239 --> 02:05:39,829
"It doesn't have to be like this, Allie,"
he said.

2037
02:05:39,829 --> 02:05:40,829
"We're adults now, we have the choice we didn't
have before.

2038
02:05:40,829 --> 02:05:41,829
We're meant to be together.

2039
02:05:41,829 --> 02:05:42,829
We always have been."

2040
02:05:42,829 --> 02:05:44,320
He walked to her side and put his hand on
her shoulder.

2041
02:05:44,320 --> 02:05:46,380
"I don't want to live the rest of my life
thinking about you and dreaming of something

2042
02:05:46,380 --> 02:05:47,380
that never happened.

2043
02:05:47,380 --> 02:05:48,770
Stay with me, Allie."

2044
02:05:48,770 --> 02:05:50,260
Tears filled her eyes.

2045
02:05:50,260 --> 02:05:53,239
"I don't know if I can," she whispered.

2046
02:05:53,239 --> 02:05:54,360
"You can, Allie...

2047
02:05:54,360 --> 02:05:58,460
I can't live my life happily knowing you're
with someone else.

2048
02:05:58,460 --> 02:06:01,060
That would kill a part of me.

2049
02:06:01,060 --> 02:06:02,929
What we have is rare.

2050
02:06:02,929 --> 02:06:05,361
It's too beautiful to just throw it away."

2051
02:06:05,361 --> 02:06:09,840
After a moment, he gently turned her towards
him, took her hands and stared at her.

2052
02:06:09,840 --> 02:06:11,350
Allie finally faced him with wet eyes.

2053
02:06:11,350 --> 02:06:17,440
After a long silence, Noah brushed the tears
from her cheeks with his fingers.

2054
02:06:17,440 --> 02:06:20,910
He saw what her eyes were telling him.

2055
02:06:20,910 --> 02:06:23,960
"You're not going to stay, are you?"

2056
02:06:23,960 --> 02:06:25,260
He smiled weakly.

2057
02:06:25,260 --> 02:06:27,869
"You want to, but you can't."

2058
02:06:27,869 --> 02:06:32,119
"Oh, Noah," she said as the tears began again,
"try to understand-"

2059
02:06:32,119 --> 02:06:36,100
He shook his head to stop her.

2060
02:06:36,100 --> 02:06:45,730
"I know what you're trying to say - I can
see it in your eyes.

2061
02:06:45,730 --> 02:06:50,710
But I don't want to understand it, Allie.

2062
02:06:50,710 --> 02:06:55,159
I don't want it to end this way.

2063
02:06:55,159 --> 02:06:58,100
I don't want it to end at all.

2064
02:06:58,100 --> 02:07:01,210
But if you leave, we both know we'll never
see each other again."

2065
02:07:01,210 --> 02:07:09,719
She leaned into him and began to cry harder
as Noah fought back his own tears.

2066
02:07:09,719 --> 02:07:12,269
He wrapped his arms around her.

2067
02:07:12,269 --> 02:07:16,570
"Allie, I can't force you to stay with me.

2068
02:07:16,570 --> 02:07:24,690
But no matter what happens in my life, I'll
never forget these last couple of days with

2069
02:07:24,690 --> 02:07:25,690
you.

2070
02:07:25,690 --> 02:07:28,519
I've been dreaming about this for years."

2071
02:07:28,519 --> 02:07:36,239
He kissed her gently, and they embraced as
they had when she first got out of her car

2072
02:07:36,239 --> 02:07:37,239
two days ago.

2073
02:07:37,239 --> 02:07:39,030
Finally, Allie let him go and wiped her tears.

2074
02:07:39,030 --> 02:07:41,320
"I have to get my things, Noah."

2075
02:07:41,320 --> 02:07:44,239
He didn't go inside with her.

2076
02:07:44,239 --> 02:07:46,429
Instead, he sat down in the rocker, exhausted.

2077
02:07:46,429 --> 02:07:53,039
He watched her go into the house and listened
as the sound of her movements faded away.

2078
02:07:53,039 --> 02:07:56,849
She emerged minutes later with everything
she'd brought and walked towards him with

2079
02:07:56,849 --> 02:07:57,849
her head down.

2080
02:07:57,849 --> 02:08:00,670
She handed him the drawing she had done yesterday
morning.

2081
02:08:00,670 --> 02:08:01,670
"Here, Noah.

2082
02:08:01,670 --> 02:08:02,710
I made this for you."

2083
02:08:02,710 --> 02:08:07,500
Noah took the drawing and unrolled it slowly.

2084
02:08:07,500 --> 02:08:09,780
The image in the foreground was a picture
of how he looked now.

2085
02:08:09,780 --> 02:08:11,540
Noah noticed that she had depicted every detail
of his face.

2086
02:08:11,540 --> 02:08:15,659
It was almost as if she'd copied it from a
recent photograph.

2087
02:08:15,659 --> 02:08:19,599
The second image was the front of the house.

2088
02:08:19,599 --> 02:08:26,139
The detail there was also incredible, as if
she had sketched it while sitting beneath

2089
02:08:26,139 --> 02:08:27,369
the oak tree.

2090
02:08:27,369 --> 02:08:28,369
"It's beautiful, Allie.

2091
02:08:28,369 --> 02:08:29,369
Thank you."

2092
02:08:29,369 --> 02:08:30,369
He attempted a smile.

2093
02:08:30,369 --> 02:08:36,659
"I told you that you were an artist."

2094
02:08:36,659 --> 02:08:39,030
She nodded with her lips pressed together.

2095
02:08:39,030 --> 02:08:41,800
It was time for her to go.

2096
02:08:41,800 --> 02:08:45,340
They walked to her car slowly, without speaking.

2097
02:08:45,340 --> 02:08:54,960
When they reached it, Noah embraced her again
until he could feel the tears in his own eyes.

2098
02:08:54,960 --> 02:09:00,170
He kissed her lips and both cheeks, then with
his finger softly brushed the places he'd

2099
02:09:00,170 --> 02:09:01,170
kissed.

2100
02:09:01,170 --> 02:09:02,170
"I love you, Allie."

2101
02:09:02,170 --> 02:09:03,170
"I love you, too."

2102
02:09:03,170 --> 02:09:06,860
Noah opened her car door and they kissed one
more time.

2103
02:09:06,860 --> 02:09:11,020
Then she slid behind the wheel, never taking
her eyes from him.

2104
02:09:11,020 --> 02:09:18,800
She put the packet of letters and her handbag
next to her on the seat and took the keys,

2105
02:09:18,800 --> 02:09:21,940
then started the engine.

2106
02:09:21,940 --> 02:09:24,289
It was almost time.

2107
02:09:24,289 --> 02:09:30,539
Noah pushed her door closed with both hands
and Allie rolled down the window.

2108
02:09:30,539 --> 02:09:38,520
She reached out her hand and Noah took it
for just a moment, moving his fingers softly

2109
02:09:38,520 --> 02:09:41,670
against her skin.

2110
02:09:41,670 --> 02:09:52,909
"Stay with me," Noah mouthed without sound,
and this for some reason hurt more than Allie

2111
02:09:52,909 --> 02:09:53,909
could expect.

2112
02:09:53,909 --> 02:09:59,210
The tears began to fall hard now, but she
couldn't speak.

2113
02:09:59,210 --> 02:10:04,130
Reluctantly, she looked away and pulled her
hand from his.

2114
02:10:04,130 --> 02:10:09,050
He fell into an almost trancelike state as
he watched the car roll slowly forwards.

2115
02:10:09,050 --> 02:10:18,309
Slowly it turned towards the road that would
take her back to town.

2116
02:10:18,309 --> 02:10:21,630
Noah felt dizzy at the sight.

2117
02:10:21,630 --> 02:10:24,949
"Don't go!" he wanted to shout.

2118
02:10:24,949 --> 02:10:36,110
But he didn't say anything, and a minute later
the only remaining signs of her were the tracks

2119
02:10:36,110 --> 02:10:37,161
that her car had left behind.

2120
02:10:37,161 --> 02:10:39,150
She was gone.

2121
02:10:39,150 --> 02:10:41,460
Forever this time.

2122
02:10:41,460 --> 02:10:42,460
Forever.

2123
02:10:42,460 --> 02:10:45,300
He closed his eyes.

2124
02:10:45,300 --> 02:10:52,559
DRIVING WITH TEARS in her eyes was difficult,
but Allie went on anyway.

2125
02:10:52,559 --> 02:10:58,599
She kept the window rolled down, thinking
the fresh air might help clear her mind.

2126
02:10:58,599 --> 02:11:04,630
By the time she reached Front Street, she
had herself a little more under control.

2127
02:11:04,630 --> 02:11:13,640
Traffic was light and she had time to watch
strangers going about their business as she

2128
02:11:13,640 --> 02:11:15,600
drove through New Bern.

2129
02:11:15,600 --> 02:11:26,159
She saw the inn just up the street drove slowly
until she reached the parking lot.

2130
02:11:26,159 --> 02:11:30,760
She turned in and saw Lon's car sitting in
the first spot.

2131
02:11:30,760 --> 02:11:40,140
Although the one next to it was open, she
passed it and picked a spot a little further

2132
02:11:40,140 --> 02:11:42,840
from the entrance.

2133
02:11:42,840 --> 02:11:52,429
She turned off the engine, then reached into
the glove compartment for a mirror and brush.

2134
02:11:52,429 --> 02:12:00,670
Looking at herself, she saw her eyes were
still red and swollen.

2135
02:12:00,670 --> 02:12:09,980
She took her purse, opened it, and once again
looked at the article that had brought her

2136
02:12:09,980 --> 02:12:11,380
here.

2137
02:12:11,380 --> 02:12:15,300
It felt impossible to her that she had arrived
only the day before yesterday.

2138
02:12:15,300 --> 02:12:19,969
It seemed like a lifetime since her dinner
with Noah.

2139
02:12:19,969 --> 02:12:33,520
She remembered the letters her mother had
given her and reached for them.

2140
02:12:33,520 --> 02:12:41,320
She untied the package and found the first
letter he had written her.

2141
02:12:41,320 --> 02:12:47,400
She began to open it, then stopped because
she could imagine what was in it.

2142
02:12:47,400 --> 02:12:51,289
Something simple, no doubt - things he'd done,
memories of the summer, perhaps some questions.

2143
02:12:51,289 --> 02:12:57,640
Instead, she reached for the last letter,
the one on the bottom of the stack.

2144
02:12:57,640 --> 02:12:58,640
The goodbye letter.

2145
02:12:58,640 --> 02:13:00,489
This one interested her far more.

2146
02:13:00,489 --> 02:13:03,460
How had he said it?

2147
02:13:03,460 --> 02:13:05,199
The envelope was thin.

2148
02:13:05,199 --> 02:13:06,860
One, maybe two pages.

2149
02:13:06,860 --> 02:13:08,600
The letter wasn't too long.

2150
02:13:08,600 --> 02:13:12,070
She turned it over and checked the back.

2151
02:13:12,070 --> 02:13:15,349
No name, just a street address in New Jersey.

2152
02:13:15,349 --> 02:13:16,809
She held her breath.

2153
02:13:16,809 --> 02:13:20,090
Unfolding it, she saw it was dated March 1935.

2154
02:13:20,090 --> 02:13:23,019
Two and a half years without a reply.

2155
02:13:23,019 --> 02:13:24,340
She began to read.

2156
02:13:24,340 --> 02:13:25,340
My dearest Allie,

2157
02:13:25,340 --> 02:13:31,030
I don't know what to say any more except that
I couldn't sleep last night because I knew

2158
02:13:31,030 --> 02:13:33,140
that it is over between us.

2159
02:13:33,140 --> 02:13:37,210
It is a different feeling for me, one that
I never expected.

2160
02:13:37,210 --> 02:13:41,320
Looking back, I suppose it is a natural ending
of our story.

2161
02:13:41,320 --> 02:13:42,320
You and I were different.

2162
02:13:42,320 --> 02:13:45,909
We came from different worlds, and yet you
were the one who taught me the value of love.

2163
02:13:45,909 --> 02:13:51,239
You showed me what it was like to care for
another, and I am a better man because of

2164
02:13:51,239 --> 02:13:52,239
it.

2165
02:13:52,239 --> 02:13:55,090
I don't want you ever to forget that.

2166
02:13:55,090 --> 02:13:58,929
I am not bitter because of what has happened.

2167
02:13:58,929 --> 02:14:06,869
I am happy we were able to come together for
even a short time.

2168
02:14:06,869 --> 02:14:12,349
And if, in some distant place in the future,
we see each other in our new lives, I will

2169
02:14:12,349 --> 02:14:17,369
smile at you with joy, and remember how we
spent a summer learning from each other and

2170
02:14:17,369 --> 02:14:18,369
growing in love.

2171
02:14:18,369 --> 02:14:23,389
And maybe, for a brief moment, you'll feel
it too, and you'll smile back and enjoy the

2172
02:14:23,389 --> 02:14:26,150
memories we will always share.

2173
02:14:26,150 --> 02:14:28,360
I love you, Allie.

2174
02:14:28,360 --> 02:14:29,360
Noah

2175
02:14:29,360 --> 02:14:34,869
She read the letter again, then put it back
into the envelope.

2176
02:14:34,869 --> 02:14:37,559
She knew she couldn't delay any longer.

2177
02:14:37,559 --> 02:14:39,480
Lon was waiting for her.

2178
02:14:39,480 --> 02:14:43,710
Her legs felt weak as she stepped out of the
car.

2179
02:14:43,710 --> 02:14:49,940
She paused and took a deep breath, and as
she started across the parking lot, she realized

2180
02:14:49,940 --> 02:14:56,929
that she still wasn't sure what she was going
to say to him.

2181
02:14:56,929 --> 02:15:08,570
And the answer didn't finally come until she
reached the door and opened it and saw Lon

2182
02:15:08,570 --> 02:15:09,960
standing in the lobby.

2183
02:15:09,960 --> 02:15:10,960
CHAPTER EIGHT

2184
02:15:10,960 --> 02:15:14,969
WINTER FOR TWO
THE STORY ends there, so I close the notebook,

2185
02:15:14,969 --> 02:15:17,929
remove my glasses and wipe my eyes.

2186
02:15:17,929 --> 02:15:24,080
I look at her now that I have finished, but
she does not look back.

2187
02:15:24,080 --> 02:15:29,059
Instead, she is staring out of the window
at the courtyard, where friends and family

2188
02:15:29,059 --> 02:15:30,059
meet.

2189
02:15:30,059 --> 02:15:36,869
I read to her this morning, as I do every
morning, because it is something I must do.

2190
02:15:36,869 --> 02:15:41,199
Not for duty but for another, more romantic
reason.

2191
02:15:41,199 --> 02:15:49,369
I wish I could explain it more fully right
now, but it's still early, and talking about

2192
02:15:49,369 --> 02:15:55,630
romance isn't really possible before lunch
any more, at least not for me.

2193
02:15:55,630 --> 02:16:00,280
Besides, I have no idea how it's going to
turn out.

2194
02:16:00,280 --> 02:16:03,900
We spend every day together now, but our nights
are spent alone.

2195
02:16:03,900 --> 02:16:08,570
The doctors tell me that I'm not allowed to
see her after dark.

2196
02:16:08,570 --> 02:16:16,289
I understand the reasons, and though I agree
with them completely I sometimes break the

2197
02:16:16,289 --> 02:16:17,289
rules.

2198
02:16:17,289 --> 02:16:27,139
Late at night when my mood is right, I leave
my room and go to hers and watch her while

2199
02:16:27,139 --> 02:16:28,260
she sleeps.

2200
02:16:28,260 --> 02:16:30,090
Of this, she knows nothing.

2201
02:16:30,090 --> 02:16:38,920
I come in and see her breathe and know that,
had it not been for her, I would never have

2202
02:16:38,920 --> 02:16:39,920
married.

2203
02:16:39,920 --> 02:16:46,319
And when I look at her face, I know that I
have meant as much to her.

2204
02:16:46,319 --> 02:16:50,710
And that means more to me than I could ever
hope to explain.

2205
02:16:50,710 --> 02:16:57,490
Sometimes, when I am standing there, I think
about how lucky I am to have been married

2206
02:16:57,490 --> 02:16:59,880
to her for almost forty-nine years.

2207
02:16:59,880 --> 02:17:04,649
She heard me snore for the first forty-five
years, but since then we have slept in separate

2208
02:17:04,649 --> 02:17:05,649
rooms.

2209
02:17:05,649 --> 02:17:06,969
I do not sleep well without her.

2210
02:17:06,969 --> 02:17:11,540
I turn and yearn for her warmth and lie there
most of the night, with my eyes open wide,

2211
02:17:11,540 --> 02:17:13,330
watching the shadows on the ceiling.

2212
02:17:13,330 --> 02:17:17,960
I sleep two hours if I am lucky, and still
I wake before dawn.

2213
02:17:17,960 --> 02:17:22,860
I shuffle towards her and sit in the chair
beside her bed.

2214
02:17:22,860 --> 02:17:25,590
My back aches when I sit.

2215
02:17:25,590 --> 02:17:31,050
I reach for her hand and take it; it's bony
and fragile.

2216
02:17:31,050 --> 02:17:32,420
It feels nice.

2217
02:17:32,420 --> 02:17:36,939
She responds - gradually her thumb begins
to rub my finger softly.

2218
02:17:36,939 --> 02:17:41,479
I do not speak until she does; this I have
learned.

2219
02:17:41,479 --> 02:17:45,739
Most days I sit in silence until the sun goes
down.

2220
02:17:45,739 --> 02:17:49,090
Minutes pass before she finally turns to me.

2221
02:17:49,090 --> 02:17:50,349
She is crying.

2222
02:17:50,349 --> 02:17:54,960
I smile and release her hand, then reach in
my pocket.

2223
02:17:54,960 --> 02:17:58,929
I take out a handkerchief and wipe at her
tears.

2224
02:17:58,929 --> 02:18:03,952
She looks at me as I do so, and I wonder what
she is thinking.

2225
02:18:03,952 --> 02:18:05,309
"That was a beautiful story."

2226
02:18:05,309 --> 02:18:07,809
A light rain begins to fall.

2227
02:18:07,809 --> 02:18:10,649
Little drops tap gently on the window.

2228
02:18:10,649 --> 02:18:13,219
I take her hand again.

2229
02:18:13,219 --> 02:18:17,739
It is going to be a good day, a very good
day.

2230
02:18:17,739 --> 02:18:18,870
A magical day.

2231
02:18:18,870 --> 02:18:19,870
I smile.

2232
02:18:19,870 --> 02:18:21,290
"Yes, it is," I tell her.

2233
02:18:21,290 --> 02:18:22,580
"Did you write it?"

2234
02:18:22,580 --> 02:18:25,149
she asks; her voice is like a whisper.

2235
02:18:25,149 --> 02:18:26,149
"Yes," I answer.

2236
02:18:26,149 --> 02:18:27,609
She turns towards the nightstand.

2237
02:18:27,609 --> 02:18:29,670
Her medicine is in a little cup.

2238
02:18:29,670 --> 02:18:30,849
Mine too.

2239
02:18:30,849 --> 02:18:38,021
Little pills, their colours are like a rainbow
so we won't forget to take them.

2240
02:18:38,021 --> 02:18:42,670
The nurses bring my pills here to her room
now.

2241
02:18:42,670 --> 02:18:45,649
"I've heard it before, haven't I?"

2242
02:18:45,649 --> 02:18:50,609
"Yes," I say again, just as I do every time.

2243
02:18:50,609 --> 02:18:52,770
I have learned to be patient.

2244
02:18:52,770 --> 02:18:54,719
She studies my face.

2245
02:18:54,719 --> 02:18:58,620
Her eyes are as green as ocean waves.

2246
02:18:58,620 --> 02:19:01,900
"It makes me feel less afraid," she says.

2247
02:19:01,900 --> 02:19:03,679
"I know," I nod.

2248
02:19:03,679 --> 02:19:06,460
She turns away, and I wait some more.

2249
02:19:06,460 --> 02:19:09,309
She releases my hand and reaches for her water
glass.

2250
02:19:09,309 --> 02:19:10,440
She takes a sip.

2251
02:19:10,440 --> 02:19:11,860
"Is it a true story?"

2252
02:19:11,860 --> 02:19:16,689
She sits up a little in her bed and takes
another drink.

2253
02:19:16,689 --> 02:19:18,819
Her body is still strong.

2254
02:19:18,819 --> 02:19:21,800
"I mean, did you know these people?"

2255
02:19:21,800 --> 02:19:23,510
"Yes," I say again.

2256
02:19:23,510 --> 02:19:26,910
I could say more, but usually I don't.

2257
02:19:26,910 --> 02:19:28,609
She is still beautiful.

2258
02:19:28,609 --> 02:19:30,319
She asks the obvious.

2259
02:19:30,319 --> 02:19:33,309
"Well, which one did she finally marry?"

2260
02:19:33,309 --> 02:19:37,389
I answer, "The one who was right for her."

2261
02:19:37,389 --> 02:19:38,719
"Which one was that?"

2262
02:19:38,719 --> 02:19:39,719
I smile.

2263
02:19:39,719 --> 02:19:43,569
"You'll know," I say quietly, "by the end
of the day.

2264
02:19:43,569 --> 02:19:44,569
You'll know."

2265
02:19:44,569 --> 02:19:46,920
She does not question me further.

2266
02:19:46,920 --> 02:19:49,010
Instead, she begins to fidget.

2267
02:19:49,010 --> 02:19:54,489
She is thinking of a way to ask me another
question, though she isn't sure how to do

2268
02:19:54,489 --> 02:19:55,489
it.

2269
02:19:55,489 --> 02:19:57,810
"I have to ask you something else," she says
finally.

2270
02:19:57,810 --> 02:19:59,660
"Whatever it is, I'll try to answer."

2271
02:19:59,660 --> 02:20:00,660
"It's hard, though."

2272
02:20:00,660 --> 02:20:04,670
She does not look at me and I cannot see her
eyes.

2273
02:20:04,670 --> 02:20:07,580
This is how she hides her thoughts.

2274
02:20:07,580 --> 02:20:09,040
Some things never change.

2275
02:20:09,040 --> 02:20:10,870
"Take your time," I say.

2276
02:20:10,870 --> 02:20:13,060
I know what she will ask.

2277
02:20:13,060 --> 02:20:16,090
She turns to me and looks into my eyes.

2278
02:20:16,090 --> 02:20:21,760
She offers a gentle smile, the kind you share
with a child, not a lover.

2279
02:20:21,760 --> 02:20:27,230
"I don't want to hurt your feelings because
you've been so nice to me, but..."

2280
02:20:27,230 --> 02:20:28,230
I wait.

2281
02:20:28,230 --> 02:20:30,010
Her words will hurt me.

2282
02:20:30,010 --> 02:20:34,300
They will tear a piece from my heart and leave
a scar.

2283
02:20:34,300 --> 02:20:35,300
"Who are you?"

2284
02:20:35,300 --> 02:20:37,689
WE HAVE LIVED at the nursing home for three
years now.

2285
02:20:37,689 --> 02:20:43,220
It was her decision to come here, because
she thought it would be easier for me.

2286
02:20:43,220 --> 02:20:47,310
We signed some papers, and received a place
to live and die in exchange for some of the

2287
02:20:47,310 --> 02:20:50,340
freedom for which we had worked a lifetime.

2288
02:20:50,340 --> 02:20:54,399
She was right to do this, of course.

2289
02:20:54,399 --> 02:21:01,569
There is no way I could make it alone, for
sickness has come to us, both of us.

2290
02:21:01,569 --> 02:21:06,109
We are in the final minutes of our lives,
and the clock is ticking.

2291
02:21:06,109 --> 02:21:07,109
Loudly.

2292
02:21:07,109 --> 02:21:10,470
I wonder if I am the only one who can hear
it.

2293
02:21:10,470 --> 02:21:16,970
A burning pain courses through my fingers,
and it reminds me that we have not held hands

2294
02:21:16,970 --> 02:21:19,530
with fingers interlocked since we moved here.

2295
02:21:19,530 --> 02:21:23,510
I am sad about this, but it is my fault, not
hers.

2296
02:21:23,510 --> 02:21:25,311
It is arthritis in the worst form.

2297
02:21:25,311 --> 02:21:30,990
But every day I take her hands despite the
pain, and I do my best to hold them because

2298
02:21:30,990 --> 02:21:33,260
that is what she wants me to do.

2299
02:21:33,260 --> 02:21:37,899
Although the Bible says man can live to be
a hundred and twenty years old, I don't want

2300
02:21:37,899 --> 02:21:38,899
to.

2301
02:21:38,899 --> 02:21:39,950
My body is falling apart.

2302
02:21:39,950 --> 02:21:43,260
My kidneys are beginning to fail and my heart
rate is decreasing every month.

2303
02:21:43,260 --> 02:21:45,729
What is worse, I have cancer again, this time
of the prostate.

2304
02:21:45,729 --> 02:21:51,080
This is my third battle with the unseen enemy,
and it will take me eventually, though not

2305
02:21:51,080 --> 02:21:52,859
till I say it is time.

2306
02:21:52,859 --> 02:21:57,109
The doctors are worried about me, but I am
not.

2307
02:21:57,109 --> 02:22:00,100
I have no time for worry now.

2308
02:22:00,100 --> 02:22:07,760
Of our five children, four are still living,
and though it is hard for them to visit, they

2309
02:22:07,760 --> 02:22:11,170
come often, and for this, I am thankful.

2310
02:22:11,170 --> 02:22:18,190
But even when they aren't here, they come
alive in my mind every day, each of them,

2311
02:22:18,190 --> 02:22:21,521
and they bring to mind the smiles and tears
that come with raising a family.

2312
02:22:21,521 --> 02:22:25,200
There are many pictures on the walls of my
room.

2313
02:22:25,200 --> 02:22:28,510
My children are my contribution to the world.

2314
02:22:28,510 --> 02:22:29,880
I am very proud.

2315
02:22:29,880 --> 02:22:36,050
Sometimes I wonder what my wife thinks of
them as she dreams, or if she thinks of them

2316
02:22:36,050 --> 02:22:38,050
at all, or if she even dreams.

2317
02:22:38,050 --> 02:22:41,680
There is so much about her I don't understand
anymore.

2318
02:22:41,680 --> 02:22:44,311
"My name," I say, "is Duke."

2319
02:22:44,311 --> 02:22:47,330
I have always been a John Wayne fan.

2320
02:22:47,330 --> 02:22:49,850
"Duke," she whispers to herself, "Duke."

2321
02:22:49,850 --> 02:22:52,279
She thinks for a moment.

2322
02:22:52,279 --> 02:22:55,200
"Yes," I say, "I'm here for you."

2323
02:22:55,200 --> 02:23:00,109
And always will be, I think to myself.

2324
02:23:00,109 --> 02:23:01,870
She flushes with my answer.

2325
02:23:01,870 --> 02:23:05,060
Her eyes become wet and red, and tears begin
to fall.

2326
02:23:05,060 --> 02:23:10,649
My heart aches for her, but there is nothing
I could do.

2327
02:23:10,649 --> 02:23:11,649
She says, "I'm sorry.

2328
02:23:11,649 --> 02:23:14,640
I don't understand anything that's happening
to me right now.

2329
02:23:14,640 --> 02:23:15,640
Even you.

2330
02:23:15,640 --> 02:23:20,260
When I listen to you talk I feel like I should
know you, but I don't.

2331
02:23:20,260 --> 02:23:22,200
I don't even know my name."

2332
02:23:22,200 --> 02:23:25,530
She wipes at her tears and says, "Help me,
Duke, help me remember who I am.

2333
02:23:25,530 --> 02:23:27,280
Or at least, who I was.

2334
02:23:27,280 --> 02:23:28,770
I feel so lost."

2335
02:23:28,770 --> 02:23:33,609
I answer from my heart, but I lie to her about
her name.

2336
02:23:33,609 --> 02:23:35,840
As I have about my own.

2337
02:23:35,840 --> 02:23:38,070
There is a reason for this.

2338
02:23:38,070 --> 02:23:41,970
"You are Hannah, a lover of life, a loyal
friend.

2339
02:23:41,970 --> 02:23:47,489
You are a dream, a creator of happiness, an
artist who has touched a thousand souls.

2340
02:23:47,489 --> 02:23:53,780
You've led a full life and wanted for nothing,
because your needs are spiritual and you have

2341
02:23:53,780 --> 02:23:55,640
only to look inside you.

2342
02:23:55,640 --> 02:24:00,870
You are kind, and you are able to see beauty
where others do not.

2343
02:24:00,870 --> 02:24:07,149
You are a teacher of wonderful lessons, a
dreamer of better things."

2344
02:24:07,149 --> 02:24:10,000
She does not respond.

2345
02:24:10,000 --> 02:24:15,120
Instead, she stares at me for a long while,
until our breathing coincides.

2346
02:24:15,120 --> 02:24:16,120
In.

2347
02:24:16,120 --> 02:24:17,120
Out.

2348
02:24:17,120 --> 02:24:18,120
In.

2349
02:24:18,120 --> 02:24:19,120
Out.

2350
02:24:19,120 --> 02:24:20,120
In.

2351
02:24:20,120 --> 02:24:21,120
Out.

2352
02:24:21,120 --> 02:24:22,120
Deep breaths.

2353
02:24:22,120 --> 02:24:23,120
I wonder if she knows I think she's beautiful.

2354
02:24:23,120 --> 02:24:24,580
"Would you stay with me a while?"

2355
02:24:24,580 --> 02:24:25,771
she finally asks.

2356
02:24:25,771 --> 02:24:28,140
I smile and nod.

2357
02:24:28,140 --> 02:24:29,569
She smiles back.

2358
02:24:29,569 --> 02:24:38,310
She reaches for my hand, takes it gently and
pulls it to her waist.

2359
02:24:38,310 --> 02:24:43,890
She stares at the knots that deform my fingers
and touches them gently.

2360
02:24:43,890 --> 02:24:47,319
Her hands are still those of an angel.

2361
02:24:47,319 --> 02:24:53,880
"Come," I say as I stand with great effort,
"let's go for a walk.

2362
02:24:53,880 --> 02:24:57,950
The air is fresh and the birds are waiting.

2363
02:24:57,950 --> 02:24:59,109
It's beautiful today."

2364
02:24:59,109 --> 02:25:02,960
I am staring at her as I say these last few
words.

2365
02:25:02,960 --> 02:25:03,960
She blushes.

2366
02:25:03,960 --> 02:25:07,560
It makes me feel young again.

2367
02:25:07,560 --> 02:25:10,540
SHE WAS FAMOUS, of course.

2368
02:25:10,540 --> 02:25:18,100
One of the best southern painters of the twentieth
century, some said, and I was, and am, proud

2369
02:25:18,100 --> 02:25:19,100
of her.

2370
02:25:19,100 --> 02:25:22,790
Her paintings are in museums around the world,
but I have kept only two for myself.

2371
02:25:22,790 --> 02:25:25,910
The first one she ever gave me and the last
one.

2372
02:25:25,910 --> 02:25:33,600
They hang in my room, and late at night I
sit and stare and sometimes cry when I look

2373
02:25:33,600 --> 02:25:34,600
at them.

2374
02:25:34,600 --> 02:25:35,600
I don't know why.

2375
02:25:35,600 --> 02:25:37,130
And so the years passed.

2376
02:25:37,130 --> 02:25:40,370
We led our lives, working, painting, raising
children, loving each other.

2377
02:25:40,370 --> 02:25:43,940
I see photos of Christmases, family trips,
of graduations and of weddings.

2378
02:25:43,940 --> 02:25:46,060
I see grandchildren and happy faces.

2379
02:25:46,060 --> 02:25:48,840
I see photos of us, our hair growing whiter,
the lines in our faces deeper.

2380
02:25:48,840 --> 02:25:51,020
A lifetime that seems so typical, yet uncommon.

2381
02:25:51,020 --> 02:25:53,790
We could not foresee the future, but who can?

2382
02:25:53,790 --> 02:25:56,729
I do not live now as I expected to.

2383
02:25:56,729 --> 02:25:58,359
But I am not bitter.

2384
02:25:58,359 --> 02:26:02,920
Our lives can't be measured by our final years,
of this I am sure.

2385
02:26:02,920 --> 02:26:07,189
Looking back, I suppose it seems obvious,
but at first, I thought her confusion understandable

2386
02:26:07,189 --> 02:26:09,489
and not unique.

2387
02:26:09,489 --> 02:26:15,000
She would forget where she placed her keys,
but who has not done that?

2388
02:26:15,000 --> 02:26:22,391
She would forget a neighbour's name, but not
someone we knew well or with whom we socialized.

2389
02:26:22,391 --> 02:26:29,640
Sometimes she would write the wrong year when
she made out her cheques, but again I took

2390
02:26:29,640 --> 02:26:33,450
it for simple mistakes that one makes when
thinking of other things.

2391
02:26:33,450 --> 02:26:37,740
But when the more obvious events occurred
I began to suspect the worst.

2392
02:26:37,740 --> 02:26:41,479
An iron in the freezer, clothes in the dishwasher,
books in the oven.

2393
02:26:41,479 --> 02:26:42,899
Other things, too.

2394
02:26:42,899 --> 02:26:50,109
But the day I found her in the car three blocks
away, crying because she couldn't find her

2395
02:26:50,109 --> 02:26:53,380
way home, was the first day I was really frightened.

2396
02:26:53,380 --> 02:26:59,160
And she was frightened, too, for when I tapped
on her window, she turned to me and said,

2397
02:26:59,160 --> 02:27:00,160
"Oh God, what's happening to me?

2398
02:27:00,160 --> 02:27:01,160
Please help me."

2399
02:27:01,160 --> 02:27:05,880
A knot twisted in my stomach, but I dared
not think the worst.

2400
02:27:05,880 --> 02:27:10,700
Six days later the doctor saw her and began
a series of tests.

2401
02:27:10,700 --> 02:27:20,830
I did not understand them then and I do not
understand them now, but I suppose it is because

2402
02:27:20,830 --> 02:27:22,110
I am afraid to know.

2403
02:27:22,110 --> 02:27:24,729
She spent almost an hour with Dr. Barnwell.

2404
02:27:24,729 --> 02:27:30,310
Finally, he called us both into his office
and sat us down.

2405
02:27:30,310 --> 02:27:41,350
She held my arm confidently, but I remember
clearly that my own hands were shaking.

2406
02:27:41,350 --> 02:27:49,900
"I'm so sorry to have to tell you this," Dr.
Barnwell began, "but you seem to be in the

2407
02:27:49,900 --> 02:27:51,710
early stages of Alzheimer's..."

2408
02:27:51,710 --> 02:27:56,670
The words echoed in my head: the early stages
of Alzheimer's...

2409
02:27:56,670 --> 02:28:03,190
My world spun in circles, and I felt her grip
tighten on my arm.

2410
02:28:03,190 --> 02:28:06,140
She whispered, almost to herself, "Oh, Noah...

2411
02:28:06,140 --> 02:28:07,140
Noah..."

2412
02:28:07,140 --> 02:28:08,890
And tears started to fall.

2413
02:28:08,890 --> 02:28:15,090
It is a dreadful disease, as empty and lifeless
as a desert.

2414
02:28:15,090 --> 02:28:18,390
It is a thief of souls and memories.

2415
02:28:18,390 --> 02:28:33,450
I did not know what to say to her as she cried,
so I simply held her and rocked her back and

2416
02:28:33,450 --> 02:28:34,450
forth.

2417
02:28:34,450 --> 02:28:36,750
I remember only bits and pieces of Dr. Barnwell's
continuing explanation.

2418
02:28:36,750 --> 02:28:38,939
"It's a degenerative brain disorder affecting
memory and personality...

2419
02:28:38,939 --> 02:28:40,250
there is no cure or therapy...

2420
02:28:40,250 --> 02:28:45,790
there's no way to tell how fast it will progress...
it differs from person to person...

2421
02:28:45,790 --> 02:28:47,790
I wish I knew more...

2422
02:28:47,790 --> 02:28:50,590
Some days will be better than others...

2423
02:28:50,590 --> 02:28:57,410
It will grow worse with the passage of time...

2424
02:28:57,410 --> 02:28:59,130
I'm sorry..."

2425
02:28:59,130 --> 02:29:01,840
It has been four years now.

2426
02:29:01,840 --> 02:29:08,160
Since then we have made the best of it, if
that is possible.

2427
02:29:08,160 --> 02:29:13,439
Allie made arrangements to leave the house
and move here.

2428
02:29:13,439 --> 02:29:16,060
She rewrote her will and sealed it.

2429
02:29:16,060 --> 02:29:23,310
She left specific burial instructions, and
they are in my desk.

2430
02:29:23,310 --> 02:29:24,770
I have not seen them.

2431
02:29:24,770 --> 02:29:29,540
And when she was finished, she began to write.

2432
02:29:29,540 --> 02:29:32,180
Letters to friends and children.

2433
02:29:32,180 --> 02:29:35,200
Letters to brothers and sisters and cousins.

2434
02:29:35,200 --> 02:29:37,470
Letters to nieces, nephews and neighbours.

2435
02:29:37,470 --> 02:29:38,470
And a letter to me.

2436
02:29:38,470 --> 02:29:44,859
I read it sometimes when I am in the mood
and, when I do, I remember Allie on cold winter

2437
02:29:44,859 --> 02:29:51,200
evenings, sitting by a fireplace with a glass
of wine at her side, reading the letters I

2438
02:29:51,200 --> 02:29:53,810
had written to her over the years.

2439
02:29:53,810 --> 02:30:00,460
She kept them, these letters, and now I keep
them, for she made me promise to do so.

2440
02:30:00,460 --> 02:30:05,420
She said I would know what to do with them.

2441
02:30:05,420 --> 02:30:12,300
She was right; I find I enjoy reading them
from time to time.

2442
02:30:12,300 --> 02:30:21,380
I see Allie now and know I've never loved
her more, but as I read the letters, I come

2443
02:30:21,380 --> 02:30:26,960
to understand that I have always felt the
same way.

2444
02:30:26,960 --> 02:30:33,410
I read them last three evenings ago.

2445
02:30:33,410 --> 02:30:41,860
It was almost two o'clock when I went to the
desk and took out the stack of letters.

2446
02:30:41,860 --> 02:30:45,851
I untied the string and found the letters
her mother had hidden so long ago and those

2447
02:30:45,851 --> 02:30:46,851
from afterwards.

2448
02:30:46,851 --> 02:30:50,870
A lifetime of letters, letters expressing
my love, letters from my heart.

2449
02:30:50,870 --> 02:30:56,800
I glanced through them with a smile on my
face, picking and choosing, and finally opened

2450
02:30:56,800 --> 02:31:00,220
a letter from a cold evening thirty-nine years
ago.

2451
02:31:00,220 --> 02:31:01,739
I read an extract:

2452
02:31:01,739 --> 02:31:06,670
Sitting next to you, while our youngest daughter
sang in the school Christmas show, I looked

2453
02:31:06,670 --> 02:31:16,250
at you and saw a pride that comes only to
those who feel deeply in their hearts, and

2454
02:31:16,250 --> 02:31:21,050
I knew that no man could be luckier than me.

2455
02:31:21,050 --> 02:31:26,100
And after our son died, the one who resembled
his mother...

2456
02:31:26,100 --> 02:31:28,200
It was the hardest time we ever went through,
and the words still ring true today:

2457
02:31:28,200 --> 02:31:35,650
In times of grief and sorrow, I will hold
you and rock you, and take your grief and

2458
02:31:35,650 --> 02:31:37,430
make it my own.

2459
02:31:37,430 --> 02:31:42,359
When you cry, I cry, and when you hurt, I
hurt.

2460
02:31:42,359 --> 02:31:51,470
And together we will try to hold back the
floods of tears and despair and make it through.

2461
02:31:51,470 --> 02:31:53,330
I pause for just a moment, remembering him.

2462
02:31:53,330 --> 02:31:57,580
He was four years old at the time, just a
baby.

2463
02:31:57,580 --> 02:32:03,630
It is a terrible thing to outlive your child,
a tragedy I wish upon no one.

2464
02:32:03,630 --> 02:32:10,660
They went on, this correspondence of life
and love, and I read dozens more, some painful,

2465
02:32:10,660 --> 02:32:11,859
most heart-warming.

2466
02:32:11,859 --> 02:32:19,460
By three o'clock, I was tired, but I had reached
the bottom of the stack.

2467
02:32:19,460 --> 02:32:24,910
There was one letter remaining, the last one
I wrote to her.

2468
02:32:24,910 --> 02:32:30,910
I moved the first page into better light and
began to read:

2469
02:32:30,910 --> 02:32:32,410
My dearest Allie,

2470
02:32:32,410 --> 02:32:37,770
The porch is silent, and for once, I am at
a loss for words.

2471
02:32:37,770 --> 02:32:49,200
It is a strange experience for me, for when
I think of you and the life we have shared,

2472
02:32:49,200 --> 02:32:52,090
there is much to remember.

2473
02:32:52,090 --> 02:32:54,399
A lifetime of memories.

2474
02:32:54,399 --> 02:32:57,810
But to put it into words?

2475
02:32:57,810 --> 02:33:05,850
I am not a poet, and yet a poem is needed
to fully express the way I feel about you.

2476
02:33:05,850 --> 02:33:10,850
So my mind drifts and I remember thinking
about our life together as I made coffee this

2477
02:33:10,850 --> 02:33:11,850
morning.

2478
02:33:11,850 --> 02:33:16,689
Kate was there, and so was Jane, and they
both became quiet when I walked into the kitchen.

2479
02:33:16,689 --> 02:33:26,010
I saw they'd been crying, and without a word
I sat myself beside them at the table and

2480
02:33:26,010 --> 02:33:27,010
held, their hands.

2481
02:33:27,010 --> 02:33:32,790
And when I looked at them, I saw you from
so long-ago, the day we said goodbye.

2482
02:33:32,790 --> 02:33:41,080
They resemble you and how you were then, beautiful
and sensitive and wounded with the hurt that

2483
02:33:41,080 --> 02:33:43,260
comes when something special is taken away.

2484
02:33:43,260 --> 02:33:49,120
And for a reason I'm not sure I understand,
I was inspired to tell them a story.

2485
02:33:49,120 --> 02:33:58,229
I called Jeff and David into the kitchen,
for they were here as well, and when the children

2486
02:33:58,229 --> 02:34:05,500
were ready I told them about us and how you
came back to me so long ago.

2487
02:34:05,500 --> 02:34:11,939
I told them about our walk, and the crab dinner
in the kitchen, and they listened with smiles

2488
02:34:11,939 --> 02:34:17,680
when they heard about the canoe ride, and
sitting in front of the fire with the storm

2489
02:34:17,680 --> 02:34:18,680
raging outside.

2490
02:34:18,680 --> 02:34:24,811
I told them about your mother warning us about
Lon the next day - they seemed as surprised

2491
02:34:24,811 --> 02:34:32,850
as we were - and yes, I even told them what
happened later that day, after you went back

2492
02:34:32,850 --> 02:34:33,850
to town.

2493
02:34:33,850 --> 02:34:36,850
That part of the story has never left me,
even after all this time.

2494
02:34:36,850 --> 02:34:43,750
Even though you described it to me only once,
I remember how impressed I was at the strength

2495
02:34:43,750 --> 02:34:45,270
you showed that day.

2496
02:34:45,270 --> 02:34:51,739
I still cannot imagine what was going through
your mind when you walked into the lobby and

2497
02:34:51,739 --> 02:34:52,739
saw Lon.

2498
02:34:52,739 --> 02:35:02,960
You told me that the two of you left the inn
and sat on a bench by the old Methodist church,

2499
02:35:02,960 --> 02:35:07,250
and that he held your hand, even as you explained
that you must stay.

2500
02:35:07,250 --> 02:35:09,210
I know you cared for him.

2501
02:35:09,210 --> 02:35:13,920
And his reaction proves to me he cared for
yur as well.

2502
02:35:13,920 --> 02:35:20,649
Even as you explained that you had always
loved me, and that it wouldn't be fair to

2503
02:35:20,649 --> 02:35:23,069
him, he did not release your hand.

2504
02:35:23,069 --> 02:35:32,060
I know he was hurt and angry, and tried for
almost an hour to change your mind, but when

2505
02:35:32,060 --> 02:35:41,271
you stood firm and said, "I can't go back
with you, I'm so sorry," he knew that you

2506
02:35:41,271 --> 02:35:43,181
had made your decision.

2507
02:35:43,181 --> 02:35:51,160
You said he simply nodded and the two of you
sat together for a long time without speaking.

2508
02:35:51,160 --> 02:35:57,700
I have always wondered what he was thinking
as he sat with you, but I'm sure it was the

2509
02:35:57,700 --> 02:36:04,470
same way I felt only a few hours before.

2510
02:36:04,470 --> 02:36:14,800
And when he finally walked you to your car,
you said he told you that I was a lucky man.

2511
02:36:14,800 --> 02:36:23,600
He behaved as a gentleman would, and I understood
then why your choice was so hard.

2512
02:36:23,600 --> 02:36:28,180
I remember that when I finished the story,
the room was quiet until Kate finally stood

2513
02:36:28,180 --> 02:36:29,180
to embrace me.

2514
02:36:29,180 --> 02:36:34,760
"Oh, Daddy," she said with tears in her eyes,
and though I expected to answer their questions,

2515
02:36:34,760 --> 02:36:36,750
they did not ask any.

2516
02:36:36,750 --> 02:36:39,940
Instead, they gave me something much more
special.

2517
02:36:39,940 --> 02:36:47,580
For the next four hours, each of them told
me how much the two of us had meant to them

2518
02:36:47,580 --> 02:36:48,580
while they were growing up.

2519
02:36:48,580 --> 02:36:51,330
One by one, they told stories about things
I had long since forgotten.

2520
02:36:51,330 --> 02:37:01,060
And by the end I was crying, because I realized
how well we had done with raising them.

2521
02:37:01,060 --> 02:37:09,880
I was so proud of them, and proud of you,
and happy about the life we have led.

2522
02:37:09,880 --> 02:37:13,260
And nothing will ever take that away.

2523
02:37:13,260 --> 02:37:14,260
Nothing.

2524
02:37:14,260 --> 02:37:19,560
I only regret that you were not here to enjoy
it with me.

2525
02:37:19,560 --> 02:37:24,979
After they left, I rocked in silence, thinking
back on our life together.

2526
02:37:24,979 --> 02:37:32,810
You are always here with me when I do so,
at least in my heart, and it is impossible

2527
02:37:32,810 --> 02:37:41,109
for me to remember a time when you were not
a part of me.

2528
02:37:41,109 --> 02:37:43,479
I love you, Allie.

2529
02:37:43,479 --> 02:37:48,229
I am who I am because of you.

2530
02:37:48,229 --> 02:37:56,510
You are every reason, every hope and every
dream I've ever had, and no matter what happens

2531
02:37:56,510 --> 02:38:00,720
to us in the future, every day we are together
is the greatest day of my life.

2532
02:38:00,720 --> 02:38:02,510
I will always be yours.

2533
02:38:02,510 --> 02:38:05,370
And, my darling, you will always be mine.

2534
02:38:05,370 --> 02:38:06,370
Noah

2535
02:38:06,370 --> 02:38:11,620
I put the pages aside and remember sitting
with Allie on our porch when she read this

2536
02:38:11,620 --> 02:38:13,610
letter for the first time.

2537
02:38:13,610 --> 02:38:15,590
It was late afternoon.

2538
02:38:15,590 --> 02:38:28,439
The sky was slowly changing colour, and as
I watched the sun go down, I thought about

2539
02:38:28,439 --> 02:38:38,380
that brief moment when day suddenly turns
into night.

2540
02:38:38,380 --> 02:38:47,069
Dusk, I realized, is just an illusion, because
the sun is either above the horizon or below

2541
02:38:47,069 --> 02:38:48,069
it.

2542
02:38:48,069 --> 02:38:55,040
And that means that day and night are linked
in a way that few things are; there cannot

2543
02:38:55,040 --> 02:39:00,750
be one without the other, yet they cannot
exist at the same time.

2544
02:39:00,750 --> 02:39:06,780
How would it feel, I wondered, to be always
together, yet forever apart?

2545
02:39:06,780 --> 02:39:09,240
I know the answer now.

2546
02:39:09,240 --> 02:39:16,620
I know what it's like to be day and night
now; always together, forever apart.

2547
02:39:16,620 --> 02:39:21,820
THERE IS BEAUTY where we sit this afternoon,
Allie and I.

2548
02:39:21,820 --> 02:39:28,310
The birds, the geese, float on the cool water,
which makes them seem larger than they really

2549
02:39:28,310 --> 02:39:29,310
are.

2550
02:39:29,310 --> 02:39:36,750
Allie too is watching them, and little by
little, we get to know each other again.

2551
02:39:36,750 --> 02:39:40,319
"It's good to talk to you.

2552
02:39:40,319 --> 02:39:48,020
I find that I miss it, even when it hasn't
been that long."

2553
02:39:48,020 --> 02:39:52,979
I am sincere and she knows this, but she is
still cautious.

2554
02:39:52,979 --> 02:39:59,439
I am a stranger.

2555
02:39:59,439 --> 02:40:10,330
"Is this something we do often?"

2556
02:40:10,330 --> 02:40:11,330
she asks.

2557
02:40:11,330 --> 02:40:19,220
"Do we sit here and watch the birds a lot?

2558
02:40:19,220 --> 02:40:25,569
I mean, do we know each other well?"

2559
02:40:25,569 --> 02:40:29,689
"Yes and no.

2560
02:40:29,689 --> 02:40:34,870
I think everyone has secrets, but we have
been acquainted for years."

2561
02:40:34,870 --> 02:40:38,040
She looks to her hands, then mine.

2562
02:40:38,040 --> 02:40:39,600
She thinks about this for a moment.

2563
02:40:39,600 --> 02:40:43,590
We do not wear our rings.

2564
02:40:43,590 --> 02:40:48,250
Again, there is a reason for this.

2565
02:40:48,250 --> 02:40:52,090
She asks, "Were you ever married?"

2566
02:40:52,090 --> 02:40:53,670
I nod.

2567
02:40:53,670 --> 02:40:54,670
"Yes."

2568
02:40:54,670 --> 02:40:57,620
"What was she like?"

2569
02:40:57,620 --> 02:40:59,069
I tell the truth.

2570
02:40:59,069 --> 02:41:01,479
"She was my dream.

2571
02:41:01,479 --> 02:41:12,390
She made me who I am, and holding her in my
arms was more natural to me than my own heartbeat.

2572
02:41:12,390 --> 02:41:15,859
I think about her all the time.

2573
02:41:15,859 --> 02:41:20,810
Even now, when I'm sitting here, I think about
her."

2574
02:41:20,810 --> 02:41:22,790
She takes this in.

2575
02:41:22,790 --> 02:41:27,680
I don't know how she feels about this.

2576
02:41:27,680 --> 02:41:33,280
Finally, she speaks softly, her voice is angelic,
sensual.

2577
02:41:33,280 --> 02:41:37,790
I wonder if she knows I think these things.

2578
02:41:37,790 --> 02:41:38,819
"Is she dead?"

2579
02:41:38,819 --> 02:41:41,170
"My wife is alive in my heart.

2580
02:41:41,170 --> 02:41:43,870
And she always will be," I answer.

2581
02:41:43,870 --> 02:41:46,180
"You still love her, don't you?"

2582
02:41:46,180 --> 02:41:47,180
"Of course.

2583
02:41:47,180 --> 02:41:48,880
But I love many things.

2584
02:41:48,880 --> 02:41:52,540
I love to sit here with you.

2585
02:41:52,540 --> 02:41:58,930
I love to share the beauty of this place with
someone I care about."

2586
02:41:58,930 --> 02:42:00,340
She is quiet for a moment.

2587
02:42:00,340 --> 02:42:04,560
She looks away so I can't see her face.

2588
02:42:04,560 --> 02:42:07,819
It has been her habit for years.

2589
02:42:07,819 --> 02:42:10,149
"Why are you doing this?"

2590
02:42:10,149 --> 02:42:12,020
No fear, just curiosity.

2591
02:42:12,020 --> 02:42:13,410
This is good.

2592
02:42:13,410 --> 02:42:17,260
I know what she means, but I ask anyway.

2593
02:42:17,260 --> 02:42:18,260
"What?"

2594
02:42:18,260 --> 02:42:21,029
"Why are you spending the day with me?"

2595
02:42:21,029 --> 02:42:22,029
I smile.

2596
02:42:22,029 --> 02:42:27,560
"I'm here because this is where I'm supposed
to be.

2597
02:42:27,560 --> 02:42:31,870
It's not complicated.

2598
02:42:31,870 --> 02:42:35,710
Both you and I are enjoying ourselves.

2599
02:42:35,710 --> 02:42:38,050
My time with you is not wasted.

2600
02:42:38,050 --> 02:42:39,490
It's what I want.

2601
02:42:39,490 --> 02:42:46,700
I sit here and we talk and I think to myself,
'What could be better than what I am doing

2602
02:42:46,700 --> 02:42:47,700
now?"'

2603
02:42:47,700 --> 02:42:52,890
She looks in my eyes, and for a moment, just
a moment, her eyes twinkle.

2604
02:42:52,890 --> 02:42:55,319
A slight smile forms on her lips.

2605
02:42:55,319 --> 02:42:58,979
"I admit I enjoy your company, but I know
nothing about you.

2606
02:42:58,979 --> 02:43:04,000
I don't expect you to tell me your life story,
but why are you so mysterious?"

2607
02:43:04,000 --> 02:43:06,830
"I read once that women love mysterious strangers."

2608
02:43:06,830 --> 02:43:09,010
"See, you haven't really answered the question.

2609
02:43:09,010 --> 02:43:11,550
You haven't answered most of my questions.

2610
02:43:11,550 --> 02:43:15,770
You didn't even tell me how the story ended
this morning."

2611
02:43:15,770 --> 02:43:16,770
I shrug.

2612
02:43:16,770 --> 02:43:19,189
We sit quietly for a while.

2613
02:43:19,189 --> 02:43:23,189
Finally, I ask, "Is it true that women love
mysterious strangers?"

2614
02:43:23,189 --> 02:43:25,260
She thinks about this and laughs.

2615
02:43:25,260 --> 02:43:29,510
Then she answers as I would, "I think some
women do."

2616
02:43:29,510 --> 02:43:30,510
"Do you?"

2617
02:43:30,510 --> 02:43:33,380
"Now don't go putting me on the spot.

2618
02:43:33,380 --> 02:43:36,960
I don't know you well enough for that."

2619
02:43:36,960 --> 02:43:39,220
She is teasing me and I enjoy it.

2620
02:43:39,220 --> 02:43:41,710
We sit and watch the world around us.

2621
02:43:41,710 --> 02:43:44,140
This has taken us a lifetime to learn.

2622
02:43:44,140 --> 02:43:52,090
It seems only the old are able to sit next
to one another and not say anything and still

2623
02:43:52,090 --> 02:43:53,120
feel happy.

2624
02:43:53,120 --> 02:43:57,239
The young, impatient, must always break the
silence.

2625
02:43:57,239 --> 02:44:00,060
It is a waste, for silence is pure.

2626
02:44:00,060 --> 02:44:01,090
Silence is holy.

2627
02:44:01,090 --> 02:44:05,520
It draws people together because only those
who are comfortable with each other can sit

2628
02:44:05,520 --> 02:44:06,520
without speaking.

2629
02:44:06,520 --> 02:44:07,910
This is the great paradox.

2630
02:44:07,910 --> 02:44:11,590
Time passes, and gradually our breathing begins
to coincide.

2631
02:44:11,590 --> 02:44:20,030
Deep breaths, relaxed breaths, and there is
a moment when she dozes off, like those comfortable

2632
02:44:20,030 --> 02:44:23,120
with one another often do.

2633
02:44:23,120 --> 02:44:29,310
When she wakes, a miracle: "Do you see that
bird?"

2634
02:44:29,310 --> 02:44:33,199
She points to it, and I can see it because
the sun is bright.

2635
02:44:33,199 --> 02:44:40,070
"Caspian stem," I say softly, and we devote
our attention to it as it flies over the river.

2636
02:44:40,070 --> 02:44:47,320
And, like an old habit rediscovered, when
I lower my arm, I put my hand on her knee

2637
02:44:47,320 --> 02:44:49,220
and she doesn't make me move it.

2638
02:44:49,220 --> 02:44:51,029
SHE IS RIGHT about my evasiveness.

2639
02:44:51,029 --> 02:44:54,069
On days like these, when only her memory is
gone, I am vague in my answers because I've

2640
02:44:54,069 --> 02:44:57,021
hurt my wife unintentionally with careless
slips of my tongue many times these past few

2641
02:44:57,021 --> 02:45:00,489
years, and I am determined not to let it happen
again.

2642
02:45:00,489 --> 02:45:05,990
So I limit myself and answer only what is
asked, to limit the pain.

2643
02:45:05,990 --> 02:45:10,950
There are days she never learns of her children
or that we are married.

2644
02:45:10,950 --> 02:45:14,990
I am sorry for this, but I will not change.

2645
02:45:14,990 --> 02:45:17,120
Does this make me dishonest?

2646
02:45:17,120 --> 02:45:25,479
Perhaps, but I have seen her crushed by the
waterfall of information that is her life.

2647
02:45:25,479 --> 02:45:33,130
Could I look myself in the mirror without
red eyes and trembling jaw and know I have

2648
02:45:33,130 --> 02:45:35,180
forgotten all that was important to me?

2649
02:45:35,180 --> 02:45:43,340
I could not and neither can she, for when
this odyssey began, that is how I began.

2650
02:45:43,340 --> 02:45:46,290
Her life, her marriage, her children.

2651
02:45:46,290 --> 02:45:47,780
Her friends and her work.

2652
02:45:47,780 --> 02:45:49,340
The days were hard on both of us.

2653
02:45:49,340 --> 02:45:55,880
I was an encyclopedia, an object without feeling,
of the who's, what's and where's in her life,

2654
02:45:55,880 --> 02:46:02,979
when in reality it is the whys, the things
I did not know and could not answer, that

2655
02:46:02,979 --> 02:46:04,819
make it all worthwhile.

2656
02:46:04,819 --> 02:46:10,790
She stared at pictures of forgotten children,
held paintbrushes that inspired nothing, and

2657
02:46:10,790 --> 02:46:14,460
read love letters that brought back no joy.

2658
02:46:14,460 --> 02:46:21,250
She became weaker over the hours, grew paler,
and ended the day worse than when it began.

2659
02:46:21,250 --> 02:46:24,640
Our days were lost and so was she.

2660
02:46:24,640 --> 02:46:26,330
So I changed.

2661
02:46:26,330 --> 02:46:30,641
I learned what is obvious to a child.

2662
02:46:30,641 --> 02:46:37,460
That life is simply a collection of little
lives, each lived one day at a time.

2663
02:46:37,460 --> 02:46:43,470
That each day should be spent finding beauty
in flowers and poetry and talking to animals.

2664
02:46:43,470 --> 02:46:47,060
That a day spent with dreaming and sunsets
and refreshing breezes cannot be better.

2665
02:46:47,060 --> 02:46:57,340
But most of all, I learned that life is for
sitting on benches next to rivers with my

2666
02:46:57,340 --> 02:47:04,439
hand on her knee and sometimes, on good days,
for falling in love.

2667
02:47:04,439 --> 02:47:05,540
"WHAT ARE you thinking?"

2668
02:47:05,540 --> 02:47:06,540
she asks.

2669
02:47:06,540 --> 02:47:07,540
It is now dusk.

2670
02:47:07,540 --> 02:47:09,649
We have left our bench and are walking slowly.

2671
02:47:09,649 --> 02:47:13,561
She is holding my arm and I am her escort.

2672
02:47:13,561 --> 02:47:16,250
It is her idea to do this.

2673
02:47:16,250 --> 02:47:18,819
Perhaps she is charmed by me.

2674
02:47:18,819 --> 02:47:22,250
Perhaps she wants to keep me from falling.

2675
02:47:22,250 --> 02:47:25,250
Either way, I am smiling to myself.

2676
02:47:25,250 --> 02:47:26,970
"I'm thinking about you."

2677
02:47:26,970 --> 02:47:37,530
She makes no response to this except to squeeze
my arm, and I can tell she likes what I said.

2678
02:47:37,530 --> 02:47:46,880
I go on, "I know you can't remember who you
are, but I can, and I find that when I look

2679
02:47:46,880 --> 02:47:50,000
at you it makes me feel good."

2680
02:47:50,000 --> 02:47:52,670
She taps my arm and smiles.

2681
02:47:52,670 --> 02:47:55,910
"You're a kind man with a loving heart.

2682
02:47:55,910 --> 02:47:59,750
I hope I enjoyed you as much before as I do
now."

2683
02:47:59,750 --> 02:48:04,960
I think about this as we walk in silence,
holding each other, past the rooms, past the

2684
02:48:04,960 --> 02:48:06,070
courtyard.

2685
02:48:06,070 --> 02:48:12,399
We come to the garden, mainly with wild flowers,
and I stop her.

2686
02:48:12,399 --> 02:48:15,520
I pick some flowers - red, pink, yellow, violet.

2687
02:48:15,520 --> 02:48:19,750
I give them to her, and she brings them to
her nose.

2688
02:48:19,750 --> 02:48:25,569
She smells them with eyes closed and she whispers,
"They're beautiful."

2689
02:48:25,569 --> 02:48:31,229
We continue our walk, me in one hand, the
flowers in another.

2690
02:48:31,229 --> 02:48:36,830
People watch us, for we are a walking miracle,
or so I am told.

2691
02:48:36,830 --> 02:48:38,439
It is true in a way.

2692
02:48:38,439 --> 02:48:42,630
By the time we reach the doorway, I am tired.

2693
02:48:42,630 --> 02:48:48,810
She knows this, so she stops me with her hand
and makes me face her.

2694
02:48:48,810 --> 02:48:53,290
She turns to me and stares for a long time.

2695
02:48:53,290 --> 02:48:55,090
"What are you doing?"

2696
02:48:55,090 --> 02:48:56,090
I ask.

2697
02:48:56,090 --> 02:49:01,790
"I don't want to forget you or this day, and
I'm trying to keep your memory alive."

2698
02:49:01,790 --> 02:49:08,770
I wonder for a moment if it will work this
time, then I know it will not.

2699
02:49:08,770 --> 02:49:09,770
It can't.

2700
02:49:09,770 --> 02:49:11,960
I do not tell her my thoughts, though.

2701
02:49:11,960 --> 02:49:14,640
I smile instead because her words are sweet.

2702
02:49:14,640 --> 02:49:15,979
"Thank you," I say.

2703
02:49:15,979 --> 02:49:16,979
"I mean it.

2704
02:49:16,979 --> 02:49:20,260
I don't want to forget you again.

2705
02:49:20,260 --> 02:49:22,670
You're very special to me."

2706
02:49:22,670 --> 02:49:25,090
My throat closes a little.

2707
02:49:25,090 --> 02:49:31,489
There is emotion behind her words, the emotions
I feel whenever I think of her.

2708
02:49:31,489 --> 02:49:37,939
I know this is why I live, and I love her
dearly at this moment.

2709
02:49:37,939 --> 02:49:45,120
How I wish I were strong enough to carry her
in my arms to paradise.

2710
02:49:45,120 --> 02:49:49,750
"Don't try to say anything," she tells me.

2711
02:49:49,750 --> 02:49:52,649
"Let's just feel the moment."

2712
02:49:52,649 --> 02:49:55,550
And I do, and I feel heaven.

2713
02:49:55,550 --> 02:50:02,029
HER DISEASE is worse now than it was in the
beginning, though Allie is different from

2714
02:50:02,029 --> 02:50:03,029
most.

2715
02:50:03,029 --> 02:50:07,680
There are three others with the disease here,
and they are the sum of my practical experience

2716
02:50:07,680 --> 02:50:08,680
of it.

2717
02:50:08,680 --> 02:50:13,050
They, unlike Allie, are in the most advanced
stages of Alzheimer's and are almost completely

2718
02:50:13,050 --> 02:50:14,050
lost.

2719
02:50:14,050 --> 02:50:15,050
They wake up hallucinating and confused.

2720
02:50:15,050 --> 02:50:17,600
They seldom recognize the people who love
them.

2721
02:50:17,600 --> 02:50:23,290
It is a trying disease, and this is why it
is hard for their children and mine to visit.

2722
02:50:23,290 --> 02:50:25,060
Allie, of course, has her own problems.

2723
02:50:25,060 --> 02:50:29,399
She is terribly afraid in the mornings and
cries inconsolably.

2724
02:50:29,399 --> 02:50:42,600
She sees tiny people, like gnomes, I think,
watching her, and she screams at them to get

2725
02:50:42,600 --> 02:50:43,600
away.

2726
02:50:43,600 --> 02:50:49,100
She bathes willingly but doesn't want to eat
regularly.

2727
02:50:49,100 --> 02:50:57,399
She is thin now, much too thin in my opinion,
and on good days, I do my best to fatten her

2728
02:50:57,399 --> 02:50:58,399
up.

2729
02:50:58,399 --> 02:51:00,199
But this is where the similarity ends.

2730
02:51:00,199 --> 02:51:05,050
This is why Allie is considered a miracle,
because sometimes, just sometimes, after I

2731
02:51:05,050 --> 02:51:07,830
read to her, her condition isn't so bad.

2732
02:51:07,830 --> 02:51:09,910
There is no explanation for this.

2733
02:51:09,910 --> 02:51:13,029
"It's impossible," the doctors say, "she cannot
have Alzheimer's."

2734
02:51:13,029 --> 02:51:14,060
But she does.

2735
02:51:14,060 --> 02:51:17,880
On most days and every morning, there can
be no doubt.

2736
02:51:17,880 --> 02:51:20,300
But why, then, is her condition different?

2737
02:51:20,300 --> 02:51:23,080
Why does she sometimes change after I read?

2738
02:51:23,080 --> 02:51:29,069
I tell the doctors the reason - I know it
in my heart, but they don't believe me.

2739
02:51:29,069 --> 02:51:33,640
Four times specialists have travelled from
Chapel Hill to find the answer.

2740
02:51:33,640 --> 02:51:36,870
Four times, they have left without understanding.

2741
02:51:36,870 --> 02:51:42,170
I tell them, "You can't possibly understand
it if you use only your science training and

2742
02:51:42,170 --> 02:51:46,290
your books," but they shake their heads and
answer, "Alzheimer's does not work like this.

2743
02:51:46,290 --> 02:51:49,989
With her condition, it's just not possible
to have a conversation or improve as the day

2744
02:51:49,989 --> 02:51:50,989
goes on.

2745
02:51:50,989 --> 02:51:51,989
Ever."

2746
02:51:51,989 --> 02:51:52,989
But she does.

2747
02:51:52,989 --> 02:51:59,300
Not every day, not most of the time, and definitely
less than she used to.

2748
02:51:59,300 --> 02:52:00,340
But sometimes.

2749
02:52:00,340 --> 02:52:03,580
And all that is gone on these days is her
memory, as if she has amnesia.

2750
02:52:03,580 --> 02:52:05,040
Her emotions are normal, her thoughts are
normal.

2751
02:52:05,040 --> 02:52:08,910
And these are the days that I know I am doing
right.

2752
02:52:08,910 --> 02:52:12,500
DINNER IS WAITING in her room when we return.

2753
02:52:12,500 --> 02:52:21,439
It has been arranged for us to eat here, as
it always is on days like these, and once

2754
02:52:21,439 --> 02:52:23,720
again, I could ask for no more.

2755
02:52:23,720 --> 02:52:26,819
The people here are good to me and I am thankful.

2756
02:52:26,819 --> 02:52:34,391
The room is lit by two candles on the table
where we will sit, and music is playing softly

2757
02:52:34,391 --> 02:52:35,850
in the background.

2758
02:52:35,850 --> 02:52:43,470
The cups and plates are plastic and the jug
is filled with apple juice, but rules are

2759
02:52:43,470 --> 02:52:45,910
rules and she doesn't care.

2760
02:52:45,910 --> 02:52:48,271
She inhales slightly at the sight.

2761
02:52:48,271 --> 02:52:49,840
Her eyes are wide.

2762
02:52:49,840 --> 02:52:51,410
"Did you do this?"

2763
02:52:51,410 --> 02:52:54,550
I nod and she walks into the room.

2764
02:52:54,550 --> 02:52:55,720
"It looks beautiful."

2765
02:52:55,720 --> 02:53:01,229
I offer my arm in escort and lead her to the
window.

2766
02:53:01,229 --> 02:53:05,479
She doesn't release it when we get there.

2767
02:53:05,479 --> 02:53:11,390
Her touch is nice, and we stand close together
on this crystal springtime evening.

2768
02:53:11,390 --> 02:53:14,290
The window is open slightly and I feel a breeze.

2769
02:53:14,290 --> 02:53:19,140
The moon has risen and we watch for a long
time as the evening sky unfolds.

2770
02:53:19,140 --> 02:53:23,640
"I've never seen anything so beautiful, I'm
sure of it," she says.

2771
02:53:23,640 --> 02:53:27,770
"I haven't, either," I say, but I am looking
at her.

2772
02:53:27,770 --> 02:53:31,720
She knows what I mean and I see her smile.

2773
02:53:31,720 --> 02:53:39,109
A moment later she whispers, "I think I know
who Allie went with at the end of the story."

2774
02:53:39,109 --> 02:53:40,109
"Who?"

2775
02:53:40,109 --> 02:53:41,109
"She went with Noah."

2776
02:53:41,109 --> 02:53:42,109
"You're sure?"

2777
02:53:42,109 --> 02:53:43,109
"Absolutely."

2778
02:53:43,109 --> 02:53:44,109
I smile and nod.

2779
02:53:44,109 --> 02:53:48,100
"Yes, she did," I say softly, and she smiles
back; her face is radiant.

2780
02:53:48,100 --> 02:53:50,649
She sits and I sit opposite her.

2781
02:53:50,649 --> 02:53:57,220
She offers her hand across the table and I
take it in mine, and I feel her thumb begin

2782
02:53:57,220 --> 02:53:59,890
to move as it did so many years ago.

2783
02:53:59,890 --> 02:54:08,200
I stare at her for a long time, living and
reliving the moments of my life, remembering

2784
02:54:08,200 --> 02:54:10,910
it all and making it real.

2785
02:54:10,910 --> 02:54:18,580
I feel my throat begin to tighten and once
again, I realize how much I love her.

2786
02:54:18,580 --> 02:54:22,189
My voice is shaky when I finally speak.

2787
02:54:22,189 --> 02:54:24,439
"You're so beautiful," I say.

2788
02:54:24,439 --> 02:54:30,370
I can see in her eyes that she knows how I
feel about her and what I really mean by my

2789
02:54:30,370 --> 02:54:31,370
words.

2790
02:54:31,370 --> 02:54:32,370
She does not respond.

2791
02:54:32,370 --> 02:54:35,189
Instead, she lowers her eyes and I wonder
what she's thinking.

2792
02:54:35,189 --> 02:54:36,319
I gently squeeze her hand.

2793
02:54:36,319 --> 02:54:37,319
I wait.

2794
02:54:37,319 --> 02:54:40,090
I know her heart and I know I'm almost there.

2795
02:54:40,090 --> 02:54:41,729
And then a miracle that proves me right.

2796
02:54:41,729 --> 02:54:46,939
As Glenn Miller plays softly in the room,
I watch as she gradually gives in to the feelings

2797
02:54:46,939 --> 02:54:47,939
inside her.

2798
02:54:47,939 --> 02:54:51,620
I see a warm smile begin to form on her lips,
the kind that makes it all worthwhile, and

2799
02:54:51,620 --> 02:54:52,620
I watch as she raises her hazy eyes to mine.

2800
02:54:52,620 --> 02:54:53,890
She pulls my hand towards her.

2801
02:54:53,890 --> 02:54:54,890
"You're wonderful..."

2802
02:54:54,890 --> 02:54:58,811
she says softly, and at that moment she falls
in love with me, too; this I know, for I have

2803
02:54:58,811 --> 02:55:02,900
seen the signs a thousand times.

2804
02:55:02,900 --> 02:55:08,250
She says nothing else, she doesn't have to,
and she gives me a look from another lifetime

2805
02:55:08,250 --> 02:55:09,850
that makes me whole again.

2806
02:55:09,850 --> 02:55:15,370
I smile back, and we stare at each other with
the feelings inside us rolling like ocean

2807
02:55:15,370 --> 02:55:16,370
waves.

2808
02:55:16,370 --> 02:55:23,439
I look about the room, then back at Allie,
and the way she's looking at me makes me warm.

2809
02:55:23,439 --> 02:55:24,949
And suddenly I feel young again.

2810
02:55:24,949 --> 02:55:27,960
I'm no longer cold or aching, or almost blind
with cataracts.

2811
02:55:27,960 --> 02:55:31,100
I'm strong and proud and the luckiest man
alive.

2812
02:55:31,100 --> 02:55:37,370
By the time the candles have burned down a
third, I am ready to break the silence.

2813
02:55:37,370 --> 02:55:41,630
I say, "I love you deeply and I hope you know
that."

2814
02:55:41,630 --> 02:55:44,439
"Of course I do," she says.

2815
02:55:44,439 --> 02:55:45,590
"I've always loved you, Noah."

2816
02:55:45,590 --> 02:55:46,590
Noah, I hear again.

2817
02:55:46,590 --> 02:55:48,689
The word echoes in my head.

2818
02:55:48,689 --> 02:55:49,689
Noah...

2819
02:55:49,689 --> 02:55:50,689
Noah.

2820
02:55:50,689 --> 02:55:52,410
She knows, I think to myself, she knows who
I am...

2821
02:55:52,410 --> 02:55:53,410
She knows...

2822
02:55:53,410 --> 02:56:00,720
Such a tiny thing, this knowledge, but for
me it is a gift from God, and I feel our lifetime

2823
02:56:00,720 --> 02:56:08,740
together, holding her, loving her, and being
with her through the best years of my life.

2824
02:56:08,740 --> 02:56:13,979
She murmurs, "Noah... my sweet Noah..."

2825
02:56:13,979 --> 02:56:21,300
And I, who could not accept the doctors' words,
have won again, at least for a moment.

2826
02:56:21,300 --> 02:56:28,569
I give up the pretence of mystery, and I kiss
her hand and bring it to my cheek and whisper

2827
02:56:28,569 --> 02:56:34,449
in her ear, "You are the greatest thing that
has ever happened to me."

2828
02:56:34,449 --> 02:56:35,449
"Oh...

2829
02:56:35,449 --> 02:56:39,899
Noah," she says with tears in her eyes, "I
love you, too."

2830
02:56:39,899 --> 02:56:44,380
IF ONLY IT would end like this, I would be
a happy man.

2831
02:56:44,380 --> 02:56:45,380
But it won't.

2832
02:56:45,380 --> 02:56:52,560
Of this, I'm sure, for soon I begin to see
the signs of worry in her face.

2833
02:56:52,560 --> 02:56:53,560
"What's wrong?"

2834
02:56:53,560 --> 02:56:55,529
I ask, and her answer comes softly.

2835
02:56:55,529 --> 02:56:56,529
"I'm so afraid.

2836
02:56:56,529 --> 02:56:58,540
I'm afraid of forgetting you again.

2837
02:56:58,540 --> 02:56:59,740
It isn't fair...

2838
02:56:59,740 --> 02:57:01,493
I just can't bear to give this up."

2839
02:57:01,493 --> 02:57:12,811
Her voice breaks as she finishes, but I don't
know what to say.

2840
02:57:12,811 --> 02:57:19,649
I know the evening is coming to an end and
there is nothing I can do to stop the inevitable.

2841
02:57:19,649 --> 02:57:21,939
In this, I am a failure.

2842
02:57:21,939 --> 02:57:24,989
I finally tell her, "I'll never leave you.

2843
02:57:24,989 --> 02:57:26,899
What we have is forever."

2844
02:57:26,899 --> 02:57:32,670
She knows this is all I can do, for neither
of us wants empty promises.

2845
02:57:32,670 --> 02:57:38,270
After dinner, I become afraid for I know the
bell has tolled this evening.

2846
02:57:38,270 --> 02:57:43,330
The sun has long since set and the thief is
about to come, and there is nothing I can

2847
02:57:43,330 --> 02:57:44,930
do to stop it.

2848
02:57:44,930 --> 02:57:51,210
So I stare at her and wait and live a lifetime
in these last remaining moments.

2849
02:57:51,210 --> 02:57:52,210
The clock ticks.

2850
02:57:52,210 --> 02:57:53,210
Nothing.

2851
02:57:53,210 --> 02:57:57,000
I take her in my arms and we hold each other.

2852
02:57:57,000 --> 02:57:58,000
Nothing.

2853
02:57:58,000 --> 02:58:03,210
I feel her tremble and I whisper in her ear.

2854
02:58:03,210 --> 02:58:04,210
Nothing.

2855
02:58:04,210 --> 02:58:09,930
I tell her for the last time this evening
that I love her.

2856
02:58:09,930 --> 02:58:11,561
And the thief comes.

2857
02:58:11,561 --> 02:58:13,050
It always amazes me how quickly it happens.

2858
02:58:13,050 --> 02:58:14,170
Even now, after all this time.

2859
02:58:14,170 --> 02:58:20,930
For as she holds me, she begins to blink rapidly
and shake her head.

2860
02:58:20,930 --> 02:58:26,150
Then, turning towards the comer of the room,
she stares for a long time, worried.

2861
02:58:26,150 --> 02:58:27,150
No!

2862
02:58:27,150 --> 02:58:28,150
My mind screams.

2863
02:58:28,150 --> 02:58:29,150
Not yet!

2864
02:58:29,150 --> 02:58:30,830
Not now... not when we're so close!

2865
02:58:30,830 --> 02:58:31,830
Not tonight!

2866
02:58:31,830 --> 02:58:32,830
Please!

2867
02:58:32,830 --> 02:58:33,830
I can't take it again!

2868
02:58:33,830 --> 02:58:34,830
It isn't fair...

2869
02:58:34,830 --> 02:58:35,979
It isn't fair...

2870
02:58:35,979 --> 02:58:39,489
But once again, it is useless.

2871
02:58:39,489 --> 02:58:42,351
"Those people," she finally says, pointing,
"are staring at me.

2872
02:58:42,351 --> 02:58:43,351
Please make them stop."

2873
02:58:43,351 --> 02:58:44,351
The gnomes.

2874
02:58:44,351 --> 02:58:45,351
My mouth goes dry.

2875
02:58:45,351 --> 02:58:46,910
It is over, I know.

2876
02:58:46,910 --> 02:58:52,270
This, the evening confusion that affects my
wife, is the hardest part of all.

2877
02:58:52,270 --> 02:58:59,609
For when it comes, she is gone, and sometimes
I wonder whether she and I will ever love

2878
02:58:59,609 --> 02:59:00,609
again.

2879
02:59:00,609 --> 02:59:04,360
"There's no one there, Allie," I say, trying
to stop the inevitable.

2880
02:59:04,360 --> 02:59:06,810
She doesn't believe me.

2881
02:59:06,810 --> 02:59:09,260
"They're staring at me.

2882
02:59:09,260 --> 02:59:11,710
You can't see them?"

2883
02:59:11,710 --> 02:59:16,640
"No," I say, and she thinks for a moment.

2884
02:59:16,640 --> 02:59:21,100
"Well, they're right there," she says, "and
they're staring at me."

2885
02:59:21,100 --> 02:59:27,990
With that, she begins to talk to herself,
and moments later, when I try to comfort her,

2886
02:59:27,990 --> 02:59:29,910
she steps back with wide eyes.

2887
02:59:29,910 --> 02:59:30,910
"Who are you?"

2888
02:59:30,910 --> 02:59:34,630
she cries in panic, her face is becoming whiter.

2889
02:59:34,630 --> 02:59:37,660
"What are you doing here?"

2890
02:59:37,660 --> 02:59:46,590
She backs away from me, her hands are in a
defensive position, and then she says the

2891
02:59:46,590 --> 02:59:49,359
most heartbreaking words of all.

2892
02:59:49,359 --> 02:59:50,479
"Go away!

2893
02:59:50,479 --> 02:59:52,710
Stay away from me!"

2894
02:59:52,710 --> 03:00:00,090
She is pushing the gnomes away from her, terrified,
not noticing my presence.

2895
03:00:00,090 --> 03:00:08,740
I stand and cross the room to her bed.

2896
03:00:08,740 --> 03:00:15,310
I am weak now, my legs ache, and there is
a strange pain in my side.

2897
03:00:15,310 --> 03:00:20,100
I press the button to call the nurses.

2898
03:00:20,100 --> 03:00:27,530
They will be here soon now, I know, and I
wait for them.

2899
03:00:27,530 --> 03:00:35,550
I sit by the bed with an aching back and start
to cry.

2900
03:00:35,550 --> 03:00:42,110
I am tired now, so I sit, alone and apart
from my wife.

2901
03:00:42,110 --> 03:00:45,399
And when the nurses come in they see two people
they must comfort.

2902
03:00:45,399 --> 03:00:56,120
A woman shaking in fear and the old man who
loves her more deeply than life itself, crying

2903
03:00:56,120 --> 03:01:02,640
softly in the comer, with his face in his
hands.

2904
03:01:02,640 --> 03:01:15,550
ON A COOL, foggy morning eight days after
she and I had spent our day together, I woke

2905
03:01:15,550 --> 03:01:24,100
early, as is my custom, and read letters written
many years before.

2906
03:01:24,100 --> 03:01:26,449
At least I tried to.

2907
03:01:26,449 --> 03:01:40,670
I couldn't concentrate too well because I
had a headache, so I put them aside and went

2908
03:01:40,670 --> 03:01:48,500
to sit in my chair by the window to watch
the sun come up.

2909
03:01:48,500 --> 03:02:01,600
It happened as I sat in the chair, just as
the sun peeped over the horizon.

2910
03:02:01,600 --> 03:02:15,080
My hand, I noticed, started to tingle, something
it had never done before.

2911
03:02:15,080 --> 03:02:18,250
I started to lift it, but I was forced to
stop when I felt a terrible headache.

2912
03:02:18,250 --> 03:02:20,359
I closed my eyes tightly.

2913
03:02:20,359 --> 03:02:23,870
My hand stopped tingling and began to go numb.

2914
03:02:23,870 --> 03:02:32,190
A shooting pain flew down my neck and into
every cell of my body, like a wave, crushing

2915
03:02:32,190 --> 03:02:33,190
and wasting everything in its path.

2916
03:02:33,190 --> 03:02:46,449
I lost my sight and I heard what sounded like
a train roaring, and I knew that I was having

2917
03:02:46,449 --> 03:02:49,660
a stroke.

2918
03:02:49,660 --> 03:02:59,880
The pain coursed through my body, and in my
last remaining moments of consciousness I

2919
03:02:59,880 --> 03:03:07,400
pictured Allie, lying in her bed, waiting
for the story I would never read, lost and

2920
03:03:07,400 --> 03:03:13,250
confused, completely and totally unable to
help herself.

2921
03:03:13,250 --> 03:03:20,430
I WAS UNCONSCIOUS on and off for days, and
in those moments when I was awake I found

2922
03:03:20,430 --> 03:03:25,499
myself fixed to machines; two bags of fluid
were hanging near the bed.

2923
03:03:25,499 --> 03:03:32,609
I drifted in and out of consciousness for
days until another foggy morning when my promise

2924
03:03:32,609 --> 03:03:35,930
to Allie stimulated my body once again.

2925
03:03:35,930 --> 03:03:44,300
I opened my eyes and saw a room full of flowers,
and their scent motivated me further.

2926
03:03:44,300 --> 03:03:52,090
I looked for the button, struggled to press
it, and a nurse arrived thirty seconds later,

2927
03:03:52,090 --> 03:03:54,710
followed closely by Dr. Barnwell.

2928
03:03:54,710 --> 03:03:58,689
"I'm thirsty," I said, and Dr. Barnwell smiled
broadly.

2929
03:03:58,689 --> 03:04:03,090
"Welcome back," he said, "I knew you'd make
it."

2930
03:04:03,090 --> 03:04:12,420
TWO WEEKS LATER I am able to leave the hospital,
though I am only half a man now.

2931
03:04:12,420 --> 03:04:19,770
The right side of my body is weaker than the
left.

2932
03:04:19,770 --> 03:04:24,380
I can't use either my cane or wheelchair,
so I must march now to my own unique rhythm

2933
03:04:24,380 --> 03:04:26,120
to keep upright.

2934
03:04:26,120 --> 03:04:34,100
Not left-right-left as in my youth, or even
the shuffle-shuffle of late, but rather slow-shuffle,

2935
03:04:34,100 --> 03:04:35,600
slide-the- right, slow-shuffle.

2936
03:04:35,600 --> 03:04:44,170
I am on a heroic adventure now when I travel
the halls.

2937
03:04:44,170 --> 03:04:50,660
When I return to my room, I know I will not
sleep.

2938
03:04:50,660 --> 03:04:54,680
I breathe deeply and smell the spring through
the open window.

2939
03:04:54,680 --> 03:05:00,580
Evelyn, one of the many nurses here, helps
me to the chair by the window.

2940
03:05:00,580 --> 03:05:04,239
She puts her hand on my shoulder and pats
it gently.

2941
03:05:04,239 --> 03:05:13,440
She says nothing, and by her silence, I know
that she is staring out of the window.

2942
03:05:13,440 --> 03:05:18,439
Then she leans forward and tenderly kisses
me on the cheek.

2943
03:05:18,439 --> 03:05:20,979
"It's good to have you back.

2944
03:05:20,979 --> 03:05:25,220
Allie's missed you and so have the rest of
us.

2945
03:05:25,220 --> 03:05:30,920
We were all praying for you because it's just
not the same around here when you're gone."

2946
03:05:30,920 --> 03:05:34,350
She smiles at me and touches my face before
she leaves.

2947
03:05:34,350 --> 03:05:35,350
I say nothing.

2948
03:05:35,350 --> 03:05:38,040
The stars are out tonight and the crickets
are singing.

2949
03:05:38,040 --> 03:05:43,949
As I sit, I wonder if anyone outside can see
me, this prisoner of flesh.

2950
03:05:43,949 --> 03:05:45,680
I watch for hours.

2951
03:05:45,680 --> 03:05:50,479
A storm is coming and in time, the sky will
turn silver.

2952
03:05:50,479 --> 03:05:55,450
Lightning cuts the wild sky and I feel my
mind drift back.

2953
03:05:55,450 --> 03:05:57,939
Who are we, Allie and I?

2954
03:05:57,939 --> 03:06:05,729
Are we ancient ivy on a tree, intertwined
so closely that we would both die if we were

2955
03:06:05,729 --> 03:06:06,729
forced apart?

2956
03:06:06,729 --> 03:06:13,860
On the desk, I see a picture of Allie, the
best one I have.

2957
03:06:13,860 --> 03:06:16,595
I reach for it and hold it inches from my
face.

2958
03:06:16,595 --> 03:06:25,320
She was forty-one when it was taken, and she
had never been more beautiful.

2959
03:06:25,320 --> 03:06:32,739
There are so many things I want to ask her,
but I know the picture won't answer, so I

2960
03:06:32,739 --> 03:06:34,040
put it aside.

2961
03:06:34,040 --> 03:06:36,240
I finally stand and turn on the lamp.

2962
03:06:36,240 --> 03:06:43,689
This is a night of memories, so I look for
and find my wedding ring.

2963
03:06:43,689 --> 03:06:46,910
It is in the top drawer.

2964
03:06:46,910 --> 03:06:50,529
I cannot wear it anymore because my knuckles
are swollen.

2965
03:06:50,529 --> 03:06:53,580
The ring is powerful - a symbol, a circle.

2966
03:06:53,580 --> 03:06:58,529
I whisper aloud, "I am still yours, Allie,
my queen, my timeless beauty.

2967
03:06:58,529 --> 03:07:03,450
You are, and always have been, the best thing
in my life."

2968
03:07:03,450 --> 03:07:11,699
It is eleven thirty and I look for the letter
she wrote to me, the one I read when the mood

2969
03:07:11,699 --> 03:07:12,699
strikes me.

2970
03:07:12,699 --> 03:07:17,700
I find it where I last left it.

2971
03:07:17,700 --> 03:07:20,260
I open it and my hands begin to tremble:

2972
03:07:20,260 --> 03:07:21,260
Dear Noah,

2973
03:07:21,260 --> 03:07:24,640
I write this letter by candlelight, as you
lie sleeping in the bedroom we have shared

2974
03:07:24,640 --> 03:07:26,960
since the day we were married.

2975
03:07:26,960 --> 03:07:37,280
I see the flame beside me and 
it reminds me of another fire from decades

2976
03:07:37,280 --> 03:07:45,840
ago, with me in your soft clothes, and I knew
then we would always be together.

2977
03:07:45,840 --> 03:07:56,780
I remember how I came back to you the day
after my mother had left.

2978
03:07:56,780 --> 03:08:05,460
I was so scared because I was sure you would
never forgive me for leaving you.

2979
03:08:05,460 --> 03:08:16,590
I was shaking as I got out of the car, but
you took it all away with your smile.

2980
03:08:16,590 --> 03:08:19,220
"How about some coffee?"

2981
03:08:19,220 --> 03:08:21,850
was all you said.

2982
03:08:21,850 --> 03:08:26,380
And you never spoke about it again in all
our years together.

2983
03:08:26,380 --> 03:08:33,920
You didn't ask questions when I left and walked
alone from time to time, during the next few

2984
03:08:33,920 --> 03:08:34,920
days.

2985
03:08:34,920 --> 03:08:45,110
When I came in with tears in my eyes, you
always knew whether I needed you to hold me

2986
03:08:45,110 --> 03:08:47,980
or to just let me be.

2987
03:08:47,980 --> 03:08:54,149
I don't know how but you did, and you made
it easier for me.

2988
03:08:54,149 --> 03:09:00,540
Later, when we went to the small chapel and
exchanged our rings, I looked into your eyes

2989
03:09:00,540 --> 03:09:03,490
and knew I had made the right decision.

2990
03:09:03,490 --> 03:09:08,860
More than that, I knew I was foolish forever
considering someone else.

2991
03:09:08,860 --> 03:09:15,120
We had a wonderful life together, and I think
about it a lot now.

2992
03:09:15,120 --> 03:09:21,630
I close my eyes sometimes and see you, sitting
on the porch and playing your guitar while

2993
03:09:21,630 --> 03:09:23,640
little ones clap to the music you create.

2994
03:09:23,640 --> 03:09:26,659
"You're a better father than you know," I
tell you later, after the children are sleeping.

2995
03:09:26,659 --> 03:09:31,840
I love you for many things, especially your
passions: love, and poetry, and fatherhood,

2996
03:09:31,840 --> 03:09:34,300
and friendship, and beauty, and nature.

2997
03:09:34,300 --> 03:09:41,660
And I am glad you have taught the children
these things, for I know their lives are better

2998
03:09:41,660 --> 03:09:42,660
for it.

2999
03:09:42,660 --> 03:09:54,060
They tell me how special you are to them,
and it makes me feel like the luckiest woman

3000
03:09:54,060 --> 03:09:55,060
alive.

3001
03:09:55,060 --> 03:10:03,550
You have taught me as well, and inspired me
and supported me in my painting, and you will

3002
03:10:03,550 --> 03:10:14,550
never know how much it has meant to me that
you were always ready to comfort and encourage

3003
03:10:14,550 --> 03:10:17,090
me.

3004
03:10:17,090 --> 03:10:25,130
You understood my need for my own studio,
my own space, and saw beyond the paint on

3005
03:10:25,130 --> 03:10:26,930
my clothes and in my hair.

3006
03:10:26,930 --> 03:10:31,409
I know it was not easy to live with something
like that.

3007
03:10:31,409 --> 03:10:32,930
And you have.

3008
03:10:32,930 --> 03:10:34,960
For forty-five years now.

3009
03:10:34,960 --> 03:10:35,979
Wonderful years.

3010
03:10:35,979 --> 03:10:44,990
You are my best friend as well as my lover,
and I do not know which side of you I enjoy

3011
03:10:44,990 --> 03:10:45,990
the most.

3012
03:10:45,990 --> 03:10:49,790
I treasure each side, just as I have treasured
our life together.

3013
03:10:49,790 --> 03:10:53,010
You have something inside you, Noah, something
beautiful and strong.

3014
03:10:53,010 --> 03:10:57,840
Kindness, that's what I see when I look at
you now, that's what everyone sees.

3015
03:10:57,840 --> 03:10:58,840
Kindness.

3016
03:10:58,840 --> 03:11:03,970
I know you think me crazy for making us write
our story before we finally leave our home,

3017
03:11:03,970 --> 03:11:07,130
but I have my reasons and I thank you for
your patience.

3018
03:11:07,130 --> 03:11:11,960
I never told you why, but now I think it is
time for you to know.

3019
03:11:11,960 --> 03:11:17,010
We have lived a lifetime most couples never
know, and when I look at you I am frightened

3020
03:11:17,010 --> 03:11:19,470
by the knowledge that all this will be ending
soon.

3021
03:11:19,470 --> 03:11:21,250
For we both know my prognosis.

3022
03:11:21,250 --> 03:11:30,160
I worry more about you than I do about me,
because I fear the pain I know you will go

3023
03:11:30,160 --> 03:11:31,160
through.

3024
03:11:31,160 --> 03:11:35,189
There are no words to express my sorrow for
this.

3025
03:11:35,189 --> 03:11:44,330
I love you so deeply, so much, that I will
find a way to come back to you despite my

3026
03:11:44,330 --> 03:11:46,620
disease, I promise you that.

3027
03:11:46,620 --> 03:11:48,970
And this is where the story comes in.

3028
03:11:48,970 --> 03:11:55,140
When I am lost and lonely, read this story
- just as you told it to the children - and

3029
03:11:55,140 --> 03:12:01,279
know that in some way I will realize it's
about us.

3030
03:12:01,279 --> 03:12:06,529
And perhaps, just perhaps, we will find a
way to be together again.

3031
03:12:06,529 --> 03:12:14,470
Please don't be angry with me on days I do
not remember you - we both know they will

3032
03:12:14,470 --> 03:12:15,470
come.

3033
03:12:15,470 --> 03:12:26,529
Know that I will always love you, and no matter
what happens, know that I have led the greatest

3034
03:12:26,529 --> 03:12:27,540
life possible.

3035
03:12:27,540 --> 03:12:29,010
My life with you.

3036
03:12:29,010 --> 03:12:33,790
Noah, wherever you are and whenever you read
this, I love you.

3037
03:12:33,790 --> 03:12:36,640
I love you deeply, my husband.

3038
03:12:36,640 --> 03:12:41,029
You are, and always have been, my dream.

3039
03:12:41,029 --> 03:12:42,029
Allie

3040
03:12:42,029 --> 03:12:47,500
I put the letter aside, rise from my desk
and find my slippers.

3041
03:12:47,500 --> 03:12:50,300
I must sit to put them on.

3042
03:12:50,300 --> 03:12:54,290
Then, standing, I cross the room and open
my door.

3043
03:12:54,290 --> 03:13:04,570
I look down the hall and see Janice seated
at the main desk, which I must pass to get

3044
03:13:04,570 --> 03:13:05,890
to Allie's room.

3045
03:13:05,890 --> 03:13:12,620
At this hour, I am not supposed to leave my
room, and Janice does not break the rules.

3046
03:13:12,620 --> 03:13:19,380
I wait to see if she will leave, but she does
not and I grow impatient.

3047
03:13:19,380 --> 03:13:23,819
I finally exit my room anyway, slow-shuffle,
slide-the-right, slow-shuffle.

3048
03:13:23,819 --> 03:13:29,240
In the end, I am discovered, but I am not
surprised.

3049
03:13:29,240 --> 03:13:31,210
I stand before her.

3050
03:13:31,210 --> 03:13:35,739
"Noah," she says, "what are you doing?"

3051
03:13:35,739 --> 03:13:40,590
"I'm taking a walk," I say.

3052
03:13:40,590 --> 03:13:43,010
"I can't sleep."

3053
03:13:43,010 --> 03:14:03,489
"You're not really going for a walk, are you?

3054
03:14:03,489 --> 03:14:13,939
You're going to see Allie."

3055
03:14:13,939 --> 03:14:16,580
"Yes," I answer.

3056
03:14:16,580 --> 03:14:27,270
"Noah, you know what happened the last time
you saw her at night.

3057
03:14:27,270 --> 03:14:30,109
You shouldn't do this."

3058
03:14:30,109 --> 03:14:32,239
"I miss her."

3059
03:14:32,239 --> 03:14:40,040
"I know you do, but I can't let you see her."

3060
03:14:40,040 --> 03:14:43,590
"It's our anniversary," I say.

3061
03:14:43,590 --> 03:14:45,720
This is true.

3062
03:14:45,720 --> 03:14:49,979
It is one year before gold.

3063
03:14:49,979 --> 03:14:52,720
Forty-nine years today.

3064
03:14:52,720 --> 03:14:56,040
"I see."

3065
03:14:56,040 --> 03:15:03,350
She looks away for a moment, and her voice
becomes softer.

3066
03:15:03,350 --> 03:15:06,460
I am surprised.

3067
03:15:06,460 --> 03:15:14,540
She has never struck me as the sentimental
type.

3068
03:15:14,540 --> 03:15:24,040
"Noah, I've seen hundreds of couples struggle
with grief, but I've never seen anyone handle

3069
03:15:24,040 --> 03:15:26,569
it like you do.

3070
03:15:26,569 --> 03:15:32,569
No one around here has ever seen anything
like it."

3071
03:15:32,569 --> 03:15:43,229
She pauses for just a moment and her eyes
begin to fill with tears.

3072
03:15:43,229 --> 03:15:56,710
"I try to think what it's like for you, how
you keep going day after day, but I can't

3073
03:15:56,710 --> 03:15:58,229
imagine it.

3074
03:15:58,229 --> 03:16:00,250
I don't know how you do it.

3075
03:16:00,250 --> 03:16:02,489
You even beat her disease sometimes.

3076
03:16:02,489 --> 03:16:07,229
Even though the doctors don't understand it,
we nurses do.

3077
03:16:07,229 --> 03:16:10,170
It's love - it's as simple as that.

3078
03:16:10,170 --> 03:16:14,090
It's the most incredible thing I've ever seen."

3079
03:16:14,090 --> 03:16:19,479
A lump has risen in my throat, and I am speechless.

3080
03:16:19,479 --> 03:16:25,540
"But, Noah, you're not supposed to do this,
and I can't let you.

3081
03:16:25,540 --> 03:16:28,700
So go back to your room."

3082
03:16:28,700 --> 03:16:33,529
Then, smiling, she says, "I'm going downstairs
for some coffee.

3083
03:16:33,529 --> 03:16:41,790
I won't be back to check on you for a while,
so don't do anything foolish."

3084
03:16:41,790 --> 03:16:50,280
She rises quickly, touches my arm and walks
towards the stairs.

3085
03:16:50,280 --> 03:17:00,409
She doesn't look back and suddenly I am alone.

3086
03:17:00,409 --> 03:17:17,320
I look at her desk and see her coffee, a full
cup, and once again, I learn that there are

3087
03:17:17,320 --> 03:17:20,771
good people in the world.

3088
03:17:20,771 --> 03:17:30,590
As I begin my way to Allie's room, I take
tiny steps, and even at that pace, my legs

3089
03:17:30,590 --> 03:17:31,620
grow tired.

3090
03:17:31,620 --> 03:17:40,479
I find I must touch the wall to keep from
falling down.

3091
03:17:40,479 --> 03:17:46,720
When I finally reach her room, my body is
weak.

3092
03:17:46,720 --> 03:17:54,170
My legs are trembling, and my eyes are blurred.

3093
03:17:54,170 --> 03:18:07,689
The door opens and light from the hallway
illuminates the bed where she sleeps.

3094
03:18:07,689 --> 03:18:13,970
She is lying with the covers halfway up.

3095
03:18:13,970 --> 03:18:20,430
After a moment, I see her roll to one side.

3096
03:18:20,430 --> 03:18:29,050
She looks small in her bed.

3097
03:18:29,050 --> 03:18:46,920
I think I hear someone coming, so I enter
her room and close the door behind me.

3098
03:18:46,920 --> 03:19:05,630
Blackness descends and 

3099
03:19:05,630 --> 03:19:22,130
I cross her floor from memory and reach the
window.

3100
03:19:22,130 --> 03:19:35,069
I open the curtains, and the moon stares back,
large and full.

3101
03:19:35,069 --> 03:19:45,970
Though I know I should not, I sit on her bed.

3102
03:19:45,970 --> 03:19:56,250
Then I reach across and gently touch her face.

3103
03:19:56,250 --> 03:20:14,529
I stroke her hair, and I feel wonder.

3104
03:20:14,529 --> 03:20:25,449
She moves and opens her eyes and I suddenly
regret my foolishness, for I know she will

3105
03:20:25,449 --> 03:20:43,069
begin to cry and scream, for this is what
she always does.

3106
03:20:43,069 --> 03:21:04,149
But I feel an urge to attempt the impossible
and lean towards her.

3107
03:21:04,149 --> 03:21:09,130
Her lips meet mine.

3108
03:21:09,130 --> 03:21:36,060
And suddenly a miracle, for I feel her mouth
open and I discover a forgotten paradise,

3109
03:21:36,060 --> 03:21:41,399
unchanged all this time, ageless like the
stars.

3110
03:21:41,399 --> 03:22:07,600
I feel the warmth of her body, I close my
eyes and become young again - a mighty ship,

3111
03:22:07,600 --> 03:22:22,250
strong and fearless, and she is my sails.

3112
03:22:22,250 --> 03:22:38,960
I gently stroke her cheek, then take her hand
in mine.

3113
03:22:38,960 --> 03:23:41,510
I kiss her lips, her cheeks, and listen as
she takes a breath.

3114
03:23:41,510 --> 03:23:48,330
She murmurs softly, "Oh, Noah...

3115
03:23:48,330 --> 03:23:57,319
I've missed you."

3116
03:23:57,319 --> 03:24:26,020
Another miracle - the greatest of all! - and
there's no way I can stop the tears as we

3117
03:24:26,020 --> 03:24:29,050
begin to slip towards heaven itself.

3118
03:24:29,050 --> 03:24:56,729
For 

3119
03:24:56,729 --> 03:25:39,120
at 
that moment, the world is full of wonder as

3120
03:25:39,120 --> 03:27:06,270
I feel her fingers reach for 

3121
03:27:06,270 --> 03:28:09,310
the buttons on my shirt and slowly, very slowly,
she begins to undo them 

3122
03:28:09,310 --> 03:35:38,739
one 

3123
03:35:38,739 --> 03:37:56,770
by one.

3124
03:37:56,770 --> 03:41:22,080
- THE 

3125
03:41:22,080 --> 03:41:22,561
END -

